{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T5wTsAauspAeRJkCNSKGtN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n     6→\n     7→public interface RoutingService {\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param routeSpecification Route specification\n    11→   * @return A list of itineraries that satisfy the specification. May be an empty list if no route\n    12→   *     is found.\n    13→   */\n    14→  List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification);\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016ndz9WECPJebHZMyG5tnbf","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"9868dc2f-e678-48aa-9ee7-523cfc09a5b6"}
