{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016ndz9WECPJebHZMyG5tnbf","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view of the codebase. Let me provide you with a complete summary of all the Java source files, SQL files, and batch job XML files that I've read.\n\n---\n\n## COMPLETE CARGO TRACKER APPLICATION CODE SUMMARY\n\nI've successfully read **104 Java source files** from the Cargo Tracker application. Below is the complete content organized by package:\n\n### **SQL & Configuration Files**\n\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/initital-data.sql`\n```sql\nINSERT INTO applicationsettings (id, sampleloaded) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n```\n\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/batch-jobs/EventFilesProcessorJob.xml`\n- Batch job configuration for processing event files\n- Defines chunk processing with EventItemReader and EventItemWriter\n- Configures upload, archive, and failed directories\n- Includes listeners for job and line parse exceptions\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.application**\n\n#### **ApplicationEvents.java** - Interface for application event notifications\n- Methods: cargoWasHandled, cargoWasMisdirected, cargoHasArrived, receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt\n\n#### **BookingService.java** - Cargo booking service interface\n- Methods: bookNewCargo, requestPossibleRoutesForCargo, assignCargoToRoute, changeDestination, changeDeadline\n- Uses validation annotations (@NotNull, @Valid, @Future)\n\n#### **CargoInspectionService.java** - Cargo inspection service\n- Method: inspectCargo(TrackingId)\n\n#### **HandlingEventService.java** - Handling event registration service\n- Method: registerHandlingEvent with completion time, tracking ID, voyage, location, and type\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal**\n\n#### **DefaultBookingService.java** - Default implementation with @Stateless\n- Implements booking operations using CargoRepository, LocationRepository, RoutingService\n- Handles booking, routing, destination changes, deadline changes\n\n#### **DefaultCargoInspectionService.java** - @Stateless implementation\n- Inspects cargo delivery status\n- Fires events for misdirected or arrived cargo\n\n#### **DefaultHandlingEventService.java** - @Stateless implementation\n- Creates handling events using HandlingEventFactory\n- Stores events and publishes cargo handled events\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util**\n\n#### **ApplicationSettings.java** - @Entity for application settings\n- Tracks whether sample data has been loaded\n\n#### **DateConverter.java** - Utility for date/time conversion\n- Formats: \"M/d/yyyy\" and \"M/d/yyyy h:m a\"\n- Methods: toDate, toDateTime, toString\n\n#### **RestConfiguration.java** - JAX-RS configuration\n- @ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\n- Configures Bean Validation error responses\n\n#### **SampleDataGenerator.java** - @Singleton @Startup\n- Loads sample locations (13 cities worldwide)\n- Loads sample voyages (5 routes)\n- Loads sample cargo data (ABC123, JKL567, DEF789, MNO456)\n- Creates handling events for demonstration\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo**\n\n#### **Cargo.java** - Main domain aggregate root (@Entity)\n- Fields: trackingId, origin, routeSpecification, itinerary, delivery\n- Methods: specifyNewRoute, assignToRoute, deriveDeliveryProgress\n- Named queries: findAll, findByTrackingId\n\n#### **CargoRepository.java** - Repository interface\n- Methods: find, findAll, store, nextTrackingId\n\n#### **Delivery.java** - @Embeddable value object\n- Represents cargo delivery status\n- Fields: transportStatus, lastKnownLocation, currentVoyage, misdirected, eta, nextExpectedActivity, isUnloadedAtDestination, routingStatus\n- Complex calculation methods for delivery state\n\n#### **HandlingActivity.java** - @Embeddable\n- Represents expected handling activity\n- Fields: type, location, voyage\n\n#### **Itinerary.java** - @Embeddable\n- Contains list of Leg objects\n- Method: isExpected(HandlingEvent) - validates events against itinerary\n\n#### **Leg.java** - @Entity\n- Represents one leg of cargo journey\n- Fields: voyage, loadLocation, unloadLocation, loadTime, unloadTime\n\n#### **RouteSpecification.java** - @Embeddable, extends AbstractSpecification\n- Fields: origin, destination, arrivalDeadline\n- Method: isSatisfiedBy(Itinerary)\n\n#### **RoutingStatus.java** - Enum\n- Values: NOT_ROUTED, ROUTED, MISROUTED\n\n#### **TrackingId.java** - @Embeddable value object\n- Unique cargo identifier\n\n#### **TransportStatus.java** - Enum\n- Values: NOT_RECEIVED, IN_PORT, ONBOARD_CARRIER, CLAIMED, UNKNOWN\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling**\n\n#### **HandlingEvent.java** - @Entity\n- Core event for tracking cargo movements\n- Fields: type, voyage, location, completionTime, registrationTime, cargo\n- Inner enum Type: LOAD, UNLOAD, RECEIVE, CLAIM, CUSTOMS\n- Named query: findByTrackingId\n\n#### **HandlingEventFactory.java** - @ApplicationScoped factory\n- Creates HandlingEvent instances\n- Validates cargo, voyage, and location existence\n- Throws: UnknownCargoException, UnknownVoyageException, UnknownLocationException\n\n#### **HandlingEventRepository.java** - Repository interface\n- Methods: store, lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo\n\n#### **HandlingHistory.java** - Value object\n- Aggregates handling events for a cargo\n- Methods: getAllHandlingEvents, getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime, getMostRecentlyCompletedEvent\n\n#### **CannotCreateHandlingEventException.java** - @ApplicationException\n- Base exception for handling event creation failures\n\n#### **UnknownCargoException.java** - Exception for unknown tracking IDs\n\n#### **UnknownLocationException.java** - Exception for unknown UN Locodes\n\n#### **UnknownVoyageException.java** - Exception for unknown voyage numbers\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location**\n\n#### **Location.java** - @Entity\n- Fields: unLocode, name\n- Static: UNKNOWN location\n- Named queries: findAll, findByUnLocode\n\n#### **LocationRepository.java** - Repository interface\n- Methods: find, findAll\n\n#### **SampleLocations.java** - Sample data\n- 13 locations: Hong Kong, Melbourne, Stockholm, Helsinki, Chicago, Tokyo, Hamburg, Shanghai, Rotterdam, Gothenburg, Hangzhou, New York, Dallas\n\n#### **UnLocode.java** - @Embeddable value object\n- UN Location Code (5 characters)\n- Pattern: [a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage**\n\n#### **Voyage.java** - @Entity\n- Fields: voyageNumber, schedule\n- Builder pattern for construction\n- Named queries: findByVoyageNumber, findAll\n\n#### **VoyageNumber.java** - @Embeddable value object\n\n#### **VoyageRepository.java** - Repository interface\n\n#### **Schedule.java** - @Embeddable\n- Contains list of CarrierMovement objects\n\n#### **CarrierMovement.java** - @Entity\n- Represents vessel movement between locations\n- Fields: departureLocation, arrivalLocation, departureTime, arrivalTime\n\n#### **SampleVoyages.java** - Sample data\n- Multiple voyages including:\n  - HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK (0100S)\n  - NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS (0200T)\n  - DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI (0300A)\n  - DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI_ALT (0301S)\n  - HELSINKI_TO_HONGKONG (0400S)\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared**\n\n#### **Specification.java** - Interface for specification pattern\n- Methods: isSatisfiedBy, and, or, not\n\n#### **AbstractSpecification.java** - Abstract base class\n- Implements composite specification operations\n\n#### **AndSpecification.java** - AND composition\n\n#### **OrSpecification.java** - OR composition\n\n#### **NotSpecification.java** - NOT decorator\n\n#### **DomainObjectUtils.java** - Utility class\n- Method: nullSafe - provides null-safe value retrieval\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service**\n\n#### **RoutingService.java** - Domain service interface\n- Method: fetchRoutesForSpecification - returns list of possible itineraries\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi**\n\n#### **CargoUpdated.java** - @Qualifier annotation for CDI events\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging**\n\n#### **LoggerProducer.java** - @ApplicationScoped\n- CDI producer for Logger instances\n- Extracts logger name from injection point\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms**\n\n#### **JmsApplicationEvents.java** - @ApplicationScoped, implements ApplicationEvents\n- Publishes events to JMS queues:\n  - CargoHandledQueue\n  - MisdirectedCargoQueue\n  - DeliveredCargoQueue\n  - HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\n\n#### **CargoHandledConsumer.java** - @MessageDriven\n- Consumes from CargoHandledQueue\n- Triggers cargo inspection service\n\n#### **DeliveredCargoConsumer.java** - @MessageDriven\n- Logs delivered cargo notifications\n\n#### **MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java** - @MessageDriven\n- Logs misdirected cargo notifications\n\n#### **RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java** - @MessageDriven\n- Logs rejected handling event registration attempts\n\n#### **HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java** - @MessageDriven\n- Processes handling event registration attempts\n- Calls HandlingEventService.registerHandlingEvent\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa**\n\n#### **JpaCargoRepository.java** - @ApplicationScoped\n- JPA implementation of CargoRepository\n- Uses EntityManager and named queries\n- Generates tracking IDs using UUID\n- Fires async @CargoUpdated events\n\n#### **JpaHandlingEventRepository.java** - @ApplicationScoped\n- JPA implementation storing and querying handling events\n\n#### **JpaLocationRepository.java** - @ApplicationScoped\n- JPA implementation for location queries\n\n#### **JpaVoyageRepository.java** - @ApplicationScoped\n- JPA implementation for voyage queries\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing**\n\n#### **ExternalRoutingService.java** - @Stateless\n- Implements RoutingService\n- Calls external graph traversal service via REST\n- Translates between domain model and pathfinder API\n- Validates itineraries against route specifications\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.pathfinder.api**\n\n#### **GraphTraversalService.java** - @Stateless JAX-RS service\n- Path: /graph-traversal/shortest-path\n- Generates random routing candidates\n- Parameters: origin, destination, deadline\n\n#### **TransitPath.java** - DTO\n- @XmlRootElement\n- Contains list of TransitEdge objects\n\n#### **TransitEdge.java** - DTO\n- Represents one segment of a route\n- Fields: voyageNumber, fromUnLocode, toUnLocode, fromDate, toDate\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal**\n\n#### **GraphDao.java** - @ApplicationScoped\n- Lists available locations\n- Returns random voyage numbers\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces**\n\n#### **Coordinates.java** - Latitude/longitude value object\n\n#### **CoordinatesFactory.java** - Factory for location coordinates\n- Maps UN Locodes to lat/long coordinates\n- Hardcoded data for 13 sample locations\n\n#### **FacesConfiguration.java** - @FacesConfig for Jakarta Faces 2.3\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade**\n\n#### **BookingServiceFacade.java** - Interface\n- Facade between domain and UI layers\n- Methods: bookNewCargo, loadCargoForRouting, loadCargoForTracking, assignCargoToRoute, changeDestination, changeDeadline, requestPossibleRoutesForCargo, listShippingLocations, listAllCargos, listAllTrackingIds\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto**\n\n#### **CargoRoute.java** - DTO for cargo routing\n- Fields: trackingId, origin, finalDestination, arrivalDeadline, misrouted, claimed, lastKnownLocation, transportStatus, legs\n\n#### **CargoStatus.java** - DTO for cargo tracking status\n\n#### **Location.java** - DTO with unLocode and name\n\n#### **Leg.java** - DTO for itinerary leg\n\n#### **RouteCandidate.java** - DTO for routing options\n\n#### **TrackingEvents.java** - DTO for tracking events\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal**\n\n#### **DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java** - @ApplicationScoped implementation\n- Orchestrates between domain services and DTOs\n- Uses assemblers to convert domain to DTOs\n- Injected services: BookingService, repositories, assemblers\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler**\n\nContains assembler classes for DTO conversion:\n- **CargoRouteDtoAssembler**\n- **CargoStatusDtoAssembler**\n- **ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler**\n- **LocationDtoAssembler**\n- **TrackingEventsDtoAssembler**\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web**\n\nJSF backing beans (@Named, @RequestScoped or @ViewScoped):\n\n#### **ListCargo.java** - Lists all cargo grouped by status\n- notRoutedCargos, routedUnclaimedCargos, claimedCargos\n\n#### **Booking.java** - Book new cargo flow\n\n#### **CargoDetails.java** - Displays cargo details\n\n#### **ChangeDestination.java** - Change cargo destination\n\n#### **ChangeDestinationDialog.java** - Dialog for destination change\n\n#### **ChangeArrivalDeadline.java** - Change deadline\n\n#### **ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java** - Dialog for deadline change\n\n#### **ItinerarySelection.java** - Select from route candidates\n\n#### **Track.java** - Track cargo by ID\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse**\n\nServer-Sent Events support:\n\n#### **RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java** - SSE endpoint\n\n#### **RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java** - Adapts cargo for SSE\n\n#### **LocationViewAdapter.java** - Adapts locations for SSE\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling**\n\n#### **HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java** - Transfer object\n- Encapsulates handling event registration data\n- Serializable for JMS transport\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest**\n\n#### **HandlingReportService.java** - @Stateless JAX-RS service\n- Path: /handling/reports\n- POST endpoint for submitting handling reports\n- Validates and converts to HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt\n\n#### **HandlingReport.java** - @XmlRootElement DTO\n- Fields: completionTime, trackingId, eventType, unLocode, voyageNumber\n- Bean Validation annotations\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.mobile**\n\n#### **EventLogger.java** - Mobile interface for event logging\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file**\n\nBatch processing components:\n\n#### **EventItemReader.java** - @Named(\"EventItemReader\")\n- Extends AbstractItemReader\n- Reads CSV files from upload directory\n- Parses lines into HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt objects\n- Supports checkpointing\n\n#### **EventItemWriter.java** - @Named(\"EventItemWriter\")\n- Extends AbstractItemWriter\n- Writes events to ApplicationEvents\n- Archives processed data to CSV\n\n#### **EventFilesCheckpoint.java** - Checkpoint data for batch processing\n\n#### **FileProcessorJobListener.java** - Batch job listener\n\n#### **LineParseExceptionListener.java** - Handles parse exceptions\n\n#### **UploadDirectoryScanner.java** - Scans for files to process\n\n#### **EventLineParseException.java** - Exception for line parsing errors\n\n---\n\n### **Package: org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web**\n\n#### **Track.java** - @Named(\"public.track\") @ViewScoped\n- Public tracking interface\n- Uses CargoTrackingViewAdapter\n- Methods: getTrackingId, setTrackingId, getCargo, getCargoAsJson, onTrackById\n\n#### **CargoTrackingViewAdapter.java** - Adapter for tracking view\n\n---\n\n## **Key Architecture Patterns**\n\n1. **Domain-Driven Design (DDD)**\n   - Clear separation of domain, application, infrastructure, and interface layers\n   - Rich domain model with aggregates (Cargo, HandlingEvent, Voyage)\n   - Specification pattern for business rules\n\n2. **Hexagonal Architecture**\n   - Domain layer at center\n   - Ports (interfaces) and adapters pattern\n   - Infrastructure adapters for persistence (JPA), messaging (JMS), and routing (REST)\n\n3. **CQRS-lite**\n   - Separation between commands (booking, handling) and queries (tracking)\n   - Different facades for different use cases\n\n4. **Event-Driven Architecture**\n   - ApplicationEvents interface\n   - JMS messaging for async processing\n   - CDI events for in-process communication\n\n5. **Technologies Used**\n   - **Jakarta EE**: EJB, CDI, JPA, JMS, Bean Validation, Batch, JAX-RS, Faces\n   - **Persistence**: JPA with named queries\n   - **Messaging**: JMS queues\n   - **Batch**: Jakarta Batch for file processing\n   - **REST**: JAX-RS for external APIs\n   - **UI**: Jakarta Faces (JSF)\n\nThis is a complete, production-quality cargo tracking application following DDD principles and enterprise Java best practices."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"5b2c4da3-dc26-4f32-bd2f-db86647baade"}
