{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_014SJx9dDaYsDVTKxABHDdcM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01B1gUGzZ72B4kVrvUwNqZ6c","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/batch-jobs/EventFilesProcessorJob.xml"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1034,"cache_read_input_tokens":11010,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1034,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2453},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"8fffefc8-a910-4018-bf90-6f6b4af83bea"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VXYtJRkw5CBf8Xg1Pug879","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     6→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Id;\n     8→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    10→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    11→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * A Cargo. This is the central class in the domain model, and it is the root of the\n    20→ * Cargo-Itinerary-Leg-Delivery-RouteSpecification aggregate.\n    21→ *\n    22→ * <p>A cargo is identified by a unique tracking ID, and it always has an origin and a route\n    23→ * specification. The life cycle of a cargo begins with the booking procedure, when the tracking ID\n    24→ * is assigned. During a (short) period of time, between booking and initial routing, the cargo has\n    25→ * no itinerary.\n    26→ *\n    27→ * <p>The booking clerk requests a list of possible routes, matching the route specification, and\n    28→ * assigns the cargo to one route. The route to which a cargo is assigned is described by an\n    29→ * itinerary.\n    30→ *\n    31→ * <p>A cargo can be re-routed during transport, on demand of the customer, in which case a new\n    32→ * route is specified for the cargo and a new route is requested. The old itinerary, being a value\n    33→ * object, is discarded and a new one is attached.\n    34→ *\n    35→ * <p>It may also happen that a cargo is accidentally misrouted, which should notify the proper\n    36→ * personnel and also trigger a re-routing procedure.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * <p>When a cargo is handled, the status of the delivery changes. Everything about the delivery of\n    39→ * the cargo is contained in the Delivery value object, which is replaced whenever a cargo is\n    40→ * handled by an asynchronous event triggered by the registration of the handling event.\n    41→ *\n    42→ * <p>The delivery can also be affected by routing changes, i.e. when a the route specification\n    43→ * changes, or the cargo is assigned to a new route. In that case, the delivery update is performed\n    44→ * synchronously within the cargo aggregate.\n    45→ *\n    46→ * <p>The life cycle of a cargo ends when the cargo is claimed by the customer.\n    47→ *\n    48→ * <p>The cargo aggregate, and the entire domain model, is built to solve the problem of booking and\n    49→ * tracking cargo. All important business rules for determining whether or not a cargo is\n    50→ * misdirected, what the current status of the cargo is (on board carrier, in port etc), are\n    51→ * captured in this aggregate.\n    52→ */\n    53→@Entity\n    54→@NamedQuery(name = \"Cargo.findAll\", query = \"Select c from Cargo c\")\n    55→@NamedQuery(\n    56→    name = \"Cargo.findByTrackingId\",\n    57→    query = \"Select c from Cargo c where c.trackingId = :trackingId\")\n    58→public class Cargo implements Serializable {\n    59→\n    60→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    61→\n    62→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    63→\n    64→  @Embedded\n    65→  @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\")\n    66→  private TrackingId trackingId;\n    67→\n    68→  @ManyToOne\n    69→  @JoinColumn(name = \"origin_id\", updatable = false)\n    70→  @NotNull\n    71→  private Location origin;\n    72→\n    73→  @Embedded\n    74→  @NotNull(message = \"Route specification is required.\")\n    75→  private RouteSpecification routeSpecification;\n    76→\n    77→  @Embedded @NotNull private Itinerary itinerary;\n    78→  @Embedded @NotNull private Delivery delivery;\n    79→\n    80→  public Cargo() {\n    81→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  public Cargo(TrackingId trackingId, RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n    85→    Validate.notNull(trackingId, \"Tracking ID is required.\");\n    86→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required.\");\n    87→\n    88→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    89→    // Cargo origin never changes, even if the route specification changes.\n    90→    // However, at creation, cargo origin can be derived from the initial\n    91→    // route specification.\n    92→    this.origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin();\n    93→    this.routeSpecification = routeSpecification;\n    94→\n    95→    this.delivery =\n    96→        Delivery.derivedFrom(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary, HandlingHistory.EMPTY);\n    97→    this.itinerary = Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY;\n    98→  }\n    99→\n   100→  public TrackingId getTrackingId() {\n   101→    return trackingId;\n   102→  }\n   103→\n   104→  public Location getOrigin() {\n   105→    return origin;\n   106→  }\n   107→\n   108→  public void setOrigin(Location origin) {\n   109→    this.origin = origin;\n   110→  }\n   111→\n   112→  public RouteSpecification getRouteSpecification() {\n   113→    return routeSpecification;\n   114→  }\n   115→\n   116→  /** @return The delivery. Never null. */\n   117→  public Delivery getDelivery() {\n   118→    return delivery;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  /** @return The itinerary. Never null. */\n   122→  public Itinerary getItinerary() {\n   123→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(this.itinerary, Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY);\n   124→  }\n   125→\n   126→  /** Specifies a new route for this cargo. */\n   127→  public void specifyNewRoute(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n   128→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required.\");\n   129→\n   130→    this.routeSpecification = routeSpecification;\n   131→    // Handling consistency within the Cargo aggregate synchronously\n   132→    this.delivery = delivery.updateOnRouting(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary);\n   133→  }\n   134→\n   135→  public void assignToRoute(Itinerary itinerary) {\n   136→    Validate.notNull(itinerary, \"Itinerary is required for assignment.\");\n   137→\n   138→    this.itinerary = itinerary;\n   139→    // Handling consistency within the Cargo aggregate synchronously\n   140→    this.delivery = delivery.updateOnRouting(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary);\n   141→  }\n   142→\n   143→  /**\n   144→   * Updates all aspects of the cargo aggregate status based on the current route specification,\n   145→   * itinerary and handling of the cargo.\n   146→   *\n   147→   * <p>When either of those three changes, i.e. when a new route is specified for the cargo, the\n   148→   * cargo is assigned to a route or when the cargo is handled, the status must be re-calculated.\n   149→   *\n   150→   * <p>{@link RouteSpecification} and {@link Itinerary} are both inside the Cargo aggregate, so\n   151→   * changes to them cause the status to be updated <b>synchronously</b>, but changes to the\n   152→   * delivery history (when a cargo is handled) cause the status update to happen\n   153→   * <b>asynchronously</b> since {@link HandlingEvent} is in a different aggregate.\n   154→   *\n   155→   * @param handlingHistory handling history\n   156→   */\n   157→  public void deriveDeliveryProgress(HandlingHistory handlingHistory) {\n   158→    this.delivery = Delivery.derivedFrom(getRouteSpecification(), getItinerary(), handlingHistory);\n   159→  }\n   160→\n   161→  /**\n   162→   * @param object to compare\n   163→   * @return True if they have the same identity\n   164→   * @see #sameIdentityAs(Cargo)\n   165→   */\n   166→  @Override\n   167→  public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   168→    if (this == object) {\n   169→      return true;\n   170→    }\n   171→    if (object == null || !(object instanceof Cargo)) {\n   172→      return false;\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    Cargo other = (Cargo) object;\n   176→    return sameIdentityAs(other);\n   177→  }\n   178→\n   179→  private boolean sameIdentityAs(Cargo other) {\n   180→    return other != null && trackingId.sameValueAs(other.trackingId);\n   181→  }\n   182→\n   183→  /** @return Hash code of tracking id. */\n   184→  @Override\n   185→  public int hashCode() {\n   186→    return trackingId.hashCode();\n   187→  }\n   188→\n   189→  @Override\n   190→  public String toString() {\n   191→    return trackingId.toString();\n   192→  }\n   193→}\n   194→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"45b04b3b-7471-409b-b39d-bf1fb4d31877"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01A7rSWBkC9bn7hxXpDkamBi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus.MISROUTED;\n     4→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED;\n     5→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus.ROUTED;\n     6→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.CLAIMED;\n     7→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.IN_PORT;\n     8→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED;\n     9→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.ONBOARD_CARRIER;\n    10→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.UNKNOWN;\n    11→\n    12→import java.io.Serializable;\n    13→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    14→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n    15→import java.util.Iterator;\n    16→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    17→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n    18→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n    19→import javax.persistence.EnumType;\n    20→import javax.persistence.Enumerated;\n    21→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    22→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    23→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    24→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    25→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    26→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    27→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    28→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    29→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    30→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    31→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    32→\n    33→/**\n    34→ * The actual transportation of the cargo, as opposed to the customer requirement\n    35→ * (RouteSpecification) and the plan (Itinerary).\n    36→ */\n    37→@Embeddable\n    38→public class Delivery implements Serializable {\n    39→\n    40→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    41→\n    42→  // Null object pattern.\n    43→  public static final LocalDateTime ETA_UNKOWN = null;\n    44→  public static final HandlingActivity NO_ACTIVITY = new HandlingActivity();\n    45→\n    46→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    47→  @Column(name = \"transport_status\")\n    48→  @NotNull\n    49→  private TransportStatus transportStatus;\n    50→\n    51→  @ManyToOne\n    52→  @JoinColumn(name = \"last_known_location_id\")\n    53→  private Location lastKnownLocation;\n    54→\n    55→  @ManyToOne\n    56→  @JoinColumn(name = \"current_voyage_id\")\n    57→  private Voyage currentVoyage;\n    58→\n    59→  @NotNull private boolean misdirected;\n    60→\n    61→  private LocalDateTime eta;\n    62→\n    63→  @Embedded private HandlingActivity nextExpectedActivity;\n    64→\n    65→  @Column(name = \"unloaded_at_dest\")\n    66→  @NotNull\n    67→  private boolean isUnloadedAtDestination;\n    68→\n    69→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    70→  @Column(name = \"routing_status\")\n    71→  @NotNull\n    72→  private RoutingStatus routingStatus;\n    73→\n    74→  @Column(name = \"calculated_at\")\n    75→  @NotNull\n    76→  private LocalDateTime calculatedAt;\n    77→\n    78→  @ManyToOne\n    79→  @JoinColumn(name = \"last_event_id\")\n    80→  private HandlingEvent lastEvent;\n    81→\n    82→  public Delivery() {\n    83→    // Nothing to initialize\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  public Delivery(\n    87→      HandlingEvent lastEvent, Itinerary itinerary, RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n    88→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n    89→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n    90→    this.calculatedAt = LocalDateTime.now().truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    91→    this.lastEvent = lastEvent;\n    92→\n    93→    this.misdirected = calculateMisdirectionStatus(itinerary);\n    94→    this.routingStatus = calculateRoutingStatus(itinerary, routeSpecification);\n    95→    this.transportStatus = calculateTransportStatus();\n    96→    this.lastKnownLocation = calculateLastKnownLocation();\n    97→    this.currentVoyage = calculateCurrentVoyage();\n    98→    this.eta = calculateEta(itinerary);\n    99→    this.nextExpectedActivity = calculateNextExpectedActivity(routeSpecification, itinerary);\n   100→    this.isUnloadedAtDestination = calculateUnloadedAtDestination(routeSpecification);\n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  /**\n   104→   * Creates a new delivery snapshot based on the complete handling history of a cargo, as well as\n   105→   * its route specification and itinerary.\n   106→   *\n   107→   * @param routeSpecification route specification\n   108→   * @param itinerary itinerary\n   109→   * @param handlingHistory delivery history\n   110→   * @return An up to date delivery.\n   111→   */\n   112→  static Delivery derivedFrom(\n   113→      RouteSpecification routeSpecification, Itinerary itinerary, HandlingHistory handlingHistory) {\n   114→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required\");\n   115→    Validate.notNull(handlingHistory, \"Delivery history is required\");\n   116→\n   117→    HandlingEvent lastEvent = handlingHistory.getMostRecentlyCompletedEvent();\n   118→\n   119→    return new Delivery(lastEvent, itinerary, routeSpecification);\n   120→  }\n   121→\n   122→  /**\n   123→   * Creates a new delivery snapshot to reflect changes in routing, i.e. when the route\n   124→   * specification or the itinerary has changed but no additional handling of the cargo has been\n   125→   * performed.\n   126→   */\n   127→  Delivery updateOnRouting(RouteSpecification routeSpecification, Itinerary itinerary) {\n   128→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required\");\n   129→\n   130→    return new Delivery(this.lastEvent, itinerary, routeSpecification);\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  public TransportStatus getTransportStatus() {\n   134→    return transportStatus;\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  public void setTransportStatus(TransportStatus transportStatus) {\n   138→    this.transportStatus = transportStatus;\n   139→  }\n   140→\n   141→  public Location getLastKnownLocation() {\n   142→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(lastKnownLocation, Location.UNKNOWN);\n   143→  }\n   144→\n   145→  public void setLastKnownLocation(Location lastKnownLocation) {\n   146→    this.lastKnownLocation = lastKnownLocation;\n   147→  }\n   148→\n   149→  public void setLastEvent(HandlingEvent lastEvent) {\n   150→    this.lastEvent = lastEvent;\n   151→  }\n   152→\n   153→  public Voyage getCurrentVoyage() {\n   154→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(currentVoyage, Voyage.NONE);\n   155→  }\n   156→\n   157→  /**\n   158→   * Check if cargo is misdirected.\n   159→   *\n   160→   * <p>\n   161→   *\n   162→   * <ul>\n   163→   *   <li>A cargo is misdirected if it is in a location that's not in the itinerary.\n   164→   *   <li>A cargo with no itinerary can not be misdirected.\n   165→   *   <li>A cargo that has received no handling events can not be misdirected.\n   166→   * </ul>\n   167→   *\n   168→   * @return <code>true</code> if the cargo has been misdirected,\n   169→   */\n   170→  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n   171→    return misdirected;\n   172→  }\n   173→\n   174→  public void setMisdirected(boolean misdirected) {\n   175→    this.misdirected = misdirected;\n   176→  }\n   177→\n   178→  public LocalDateTime getEstimatedTimeOfArrival() {\n   179→    return eta;\n   180→  }\n   181→\n   182→  public HandlingActivity getNextExpectedActivity() {\n   183→    return nextExpectedActivity;\n   184→  }\n   185→\n   186→  /** @return True if the cargo has been unloaded at the final destination. */\n   187→  public boolean isUnloadedAtDestination() {\n   188→    return isUnloadedAtDestination;\n   189→  }\n   190→\n   191→  public void setUnloadedAtDestination(boolean isUnloadedAtDestination) {\n   192→    this.isUnloadedAtDestination = isUnloadedAtDestination;\n   193→  }\n   194→\n   195→  public RoutingStatus getRoutingStatus() {\n   196→    return routingStatus;\n   197→  }\n   198→\n   199→  public void setRoutingStatus(RoutingStatus routingStatus) {\n   200→    this.routingStatus = routingStatus;\n   201→  }\n   202→\n   203→  public LocalDateTime getCalculatedAt() {\n   204→    return calculatedAt;\n   205→  }\n   206→\n   207→  public void setCalculatedAt(LocalDateTime calculatedAt) {\n   208→    this.calculatedAt = calculatedAt;\n   209→  }\n   210→\n   211→  private TransportStatus calculateTransportStatus() {\n   212→    if (lastEvent == null) {\n   213→      return NOT_RECEIVED;\n   214→    }\n   215→\n   216→    switch (lastEvent.getType()) {\n   217→      case LOAD:\n   218→        return ONBOARD_CARRIER;\n   219→      case UNLOAD:\n   220→      case RECEIVE:\n   221→      case CUSTOMS:\n   222→        return IN_PORT;\n   223→      case CLAIM:\n   224→        return CLAIMED;\n   225→      default:\n   226→        return UNKNOWN;\n   227→    }\n   228→  }\n   229→\n   230→  private Location calculateLastKnownLocation() {\n   231→    if (lastEvent != null) {\n   232→      return lastEvent.getLocation();\n   233→    } else {\n   234→      return null;\n   235→    }\n   236→  }\n   237→\n   238→  private Voyage calculateCurrentVoyage() {\n   239→    if (getTransportStatus().equals(ONBOARD_CARRIER) && lastEvent != null) {\n   240→      return lastEvent.getVoyage();\n   241→    } else {\n   242→      return null;\n   243→    }\n   244→  }\n   245→\n   246→  private boolean calculateMisdirectionStatus(Itinerary itinerary) {\n   247→    if (lastEvent == null) {\n   248→      return false;\n   249→    } else {\n   250→      return !itinerary.isExpected(lastEvent);\n   251→    }\n   252→  }\n   253→\n   254→  private LocalDateTime calculateEta(Itinerary itinerary) {\n   255→    if (onTrack()) {\n   256→      // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   257→      // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   258→      return itinerary.getFinalArrivalDate().truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   259→    } else {\n   260→      return ETA_UNKOWN;\n   261→    }\n   262→  }\n   263→\n   264→  private HandlingActivity calculateNextExpectedActivity(\n   265→      RouteSpecification routeSpecification, Itinerary itinerary) {\n   266→    if (!onTrack()) {\n   267→      return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   268→    }\n   269→\n   270→    if (lastEvent == null) {\n   271→      return new HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE, routeSpecification.getOrigin());\n   272→    }\n   273→\n   274→    switch (lastEvent.getType()) {\n   275→      case LOAD:\n   276→        for (Leg leg : itinerary.getLegs()) {\n   277→          if (leg.getLoadLocation().sameIdentityAs(lastEvent.getLocation())) {\n   278→            return new HandlingActivity(\n   279→                HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD, leg.getUnloadLocation(), leg.getVoyage());\n   280→          }\n   281→        }\n   282→\n   283→        return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   284→\n   285→      case UNLOAD:\n   286→        for (Iterator<Leg> iterator = itinerary.getLegs().iterator(); iterator.hasNext(); ) {\n   287→          Leg leg = iterator.next();\n   288→\n   289→          if (leg.getUnloadLocation().sameIdentityAs(lastEvent.getLocation())) {\n   290→            if (iterator.hasNext()) {\n   291→              Leg nextLeg = iterator.next();\n   292→              return new HandlingActivity(\n   293→                  HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD, nextLeg.getLoadLocation(), nextLeg.getVoyage());\n   294→            } else {\n   295→              return new HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type.CLAIM, leg.getUnloadLocation());\n   296→            }\n   297→          }\n   298→        }\n   299→\n   300→        return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   301→\n   302→      case RECEIVE:\n   303→        Leg firstLeg = itinerary.getLegs().iterator().next();\n   304→\n   305→        return new HandlingActivity(\n   306→            HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD, firstLeg.getLoadLocation(), firstLeg.getVoyage());\n   307→\n   308→      case CLAIM:\n   309→      default:\n   310→        return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   311→    }\n   312→  }\n   313→\n   314→  private RoutingStatus calculateRoutingStatus(\n   315→      Itinerary itinerary, RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n   316→    if (itinerary == null || itinerary == Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY) {\n   317→      return NOT_ROUTED;\n   318→    } else {\n   319→      if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n   320→        return ROUTED;\n   321→      } else {\n   322→        return MISROUTED;\n   323→      }\n   324→    }\n   325→  }\n   326→\n   327→  private boolean calculateUnloadedAtDestination(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n   328→    return lastEvent != null\n   329→        && HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD.sameValueAs(lastEvent.getType())\n   330→        && routeSpecification.getDestination().sameIdentityAs(lastEvent.getLocation());\n   331→  }\n   332→\n   333→  private boolean onTrack() {\n   334→    return routingStatus.equals(ROUTED) && !misdirected;\n   335→  }\n   336→\n   337→  private boolean sameValueAs(Delivery other) {\n   338→    return other != null\n   339→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   340→            .append(this.transportStatus, other.transportStatus)\n   341→            .append(this.lastKnownLocation, other.lastKnownLocation)\n   342→            .append(this.currentVoyage, other.currentVoyage)\n   343→            .append(this.misdirected, other.misdirected)\n   344→            .append(this.eta, other.eta)\n   345→            .append(this.nextExpectedActivity, other.nextExpectedActivity)\n   346→            .append(this.isUnloadedAtDestination, other.isUnloadedAtDestination)\n   347→            .append(this.routingStatus, other.routingStatus)\n   348→            .append(this.calculatedAt, other.calculatedAt)\n   349→            .append(this.lastEvent, other.lastEvent)\n   350→            .isEquals();\n   351→  }\n   352→\n   353→  @Override\n   354→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   355→    if (this == o) {\n   356→      return true;\n   357→    }\n   358→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Delivery)) {\n   359→      return false;\n   360→    }\n   361→\n   362→    Delivery other = (Delivery) o;\n   363→\n   364→    return sameValueAs(other);\n   365→  }\n   366→\n   367→  @Override\n   368→  public int hashCode() {\n   369→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   370→        .append(transportStatus)\n   371→        .append(lastKnownLocation)\n   372→        .append(currentVoyage)\n   373→        .append(misdirected)\n   374→        .append(eta)\n   375→        .append(nextExpectedActivity)\n   376→        .append(isUnloadedAtDestination)\n   377→        .append(routingStatus)\n   378→        .append(calculatedAt)\n   379→        .append(lastEvent)\n   380→        .toHashCode();\n   381→  }\n   382→}\n   383→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"ffa96c19-71d8-4a18-b61d-23eb02832682"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MsiyhLHXzugX94ciN4HEqE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import javax.persistence.EnumType;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Enumerated;\n     8→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    10→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    11→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * A handling activity represents how and where a cargo can be handled, and can be used to express\n    20→ * predictions about what is expected to happen to a cargo in the future.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Embeddable\n    23→public class HandlingActivity implements Serializable {\n    24→\n    25→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    26→\n    27→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    28→  @Column(name = \"next_expected_handling_event_type\")\n    29→  @NotNull(message = \"Handling event type is required.\")\n    30→  private HandlingEvent.Type type;\n    31→\n    32→  @ManyToOne\n    33→  @JoinColumn(name = \"next_expected_location_id\")\n    34→  @NotNull(message = \"Location is required.\")\n    35→  private Location location;\n    36→\n    37→  @ManyToOne\n    38→  @JoinColumn(name = \"next_expected_voyage_id\")\n    39→  private Voyage voyage;\n    40→\n    41→  public HandlingActivity() {}\n    42→\n    43→  public HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type type, Location location) {\n    44→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required.\");\n    45→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required.\");\n    46→\n    47→    this.type = type;\n    48→    this.location = location;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type type, Location location, Voyage voyage) {\n    52→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n    53→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n    54→    Validate.notNull(voyage, \"Voyage is required\");\n    55→\n    56→    this.type = type;\n    57→    this.location = location;\n    58→    this.voyage = voyage;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public HandlingEvent.Type getType() {\n    62→    return type;\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public Location getLocation() {\n    66→    return location;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n    70→    return voyage;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  private boolean sameValueAs(HandlingActivity other) {\n    74→    return other != null\n    75→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n    76→            .append(this.type, other.type)\n    77→            .append(this.location, other.location)\n    78→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n    79→            .isEquals();\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  @Override\n    83→  public int hashCode() {\n    84→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n    85→        .append(this.type)\n    86→        .append(this.location)\n    87→        .append(this.voyage)\n    88→        .toHashCode();\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  @Override\n    92→  public boolean equals(Object obj) {\n    93→    if (obj == this) {\n    94→      return true;\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    if (obj == null) {\n    98→      return false;\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    if (!(obj instanceof HandlingActivity)) {\n   102→      return false;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    HandlingActivity other = (HandlingActivity) obj;\n   106→\n   107→    return sameValueAs(other);\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n   111→    if (type != null) {\n   112→      return false;\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    if (location != null) {\n   116→      return false;\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    return voyage == null;\n   120→  }\n   121→}\n   122→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"7f0768c8-56db-4991-b700-8cbb5d7fb637"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S1sCV4MpMNZFFnedzc7mJP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import javax.persistence.CascadeType;\n     8→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     9→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    10→import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\n    11→import javax.persistence.OrderColumn;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    13→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    17→\n    18→@Embeddable\n    19→public class Itinerary implements Serializable {\n    20→\n    21→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    22→\n    23→  // Null object pattern.\n    24→  public static final Itinerary EMPTY_ITINERARY = new Itinerary();\n    25→\n    26→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look into why cascade delete doesn't work.\n    27→  @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL)\n    28→  @JoinColumn(name = \"cargo_id\")\n    29→  @OrderColumn(name = \"leg_order\")\n    30→  @Size(min = 1)\n    31→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Legs must not be empty.\")\n    32→  private List<Leg> legs = Collections.emptyList();\n    33→\n    34→  public Itinerary() {\n    35→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public Itinerary(List<Leg> legs) {\n    39→    Validate.notEmpty(legs);\n    40→    Validate.noNullElements(legs);\n    41→\n    42→    this.legs = legs;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public List<Leg> getLegs() {\n    46→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(legs);\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  /** Test if the given handling event is expected when executing this itinerary. */\n    50→  public boolean isExpected(HandlingEvent event) {\n    51→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n    52→      return true;\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    switch (event.getType()) {\n    56→      case RECEIVE:\n    57→        {\n    58→          // Check that the first leg's origin is the event's location\n    59→          Leg leg = legs.get(0);\n    60→          return leg.getLoadLocation().equals(event.getLocation());\n    61→        }\n    62→\n    63→      case LOAD:\n    64→        {\n    65→          return legs.stream()\n    66→              .anyMatch(\n    67→                  leg ->\n    68→                      leg.getLoadLocation().equals(event.getLocation())\n    69→                          && leg.getVoyage().equals(event.getVoyage()));\n    70→        }\n    71→\n    72→      case UNLOAD:\n    73→        {\n    74→          // Check that the there is one leg with same unload location and\n    75→          // voyage\n    76→          return legs.stream()\n    77→              .anyMatch(\n    78→                  leg ->\n    79→                      leg.getUnloadLocation().equals(event.getLocation())\n    80→                          && leg.getVoyage().equals(event.getVoyage()));\n    81→        }\n    82→\n    83→      case CLAIM:\n    84→        {\n    85→          // Check that the last leg's destination is from the event's\n    86→          // location\n    87→          Leg leg = getLastLeg();\n    88→\n    89→          return leg.getUnloadLocation().equals(event.getLocation());\n    90→        }\n    91→\n    92→      case CUSTOMS:\n    93→        {\n    94→          return true;\n    95→        }\n    96→\n    97→      default:\n    98→        throw new RuntimeException(\"Event case is not handled\");\n    99→    }\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  Location getInitialDepartureLocation() {\n   103→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n   104→      return Location.UNKNOWN;\n   105→    } else {\n   106→      return legs.get(0).getLoadLocation();\n   107→    }\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  Location getFinalArrivalLocation() {\n   111→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n   112→      return Location.UNKNOWN;\n   113→    } else {\n   114→      return getLastLeg().getUnloadLocation();\n   115→    }\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  /** @return Date when cargo arrives at final destination. */\n   119→  LocalDateTime getFinalArrivalDate() {\n   120→    Leg lastLeg = getLastLeg();\n   121→\n   122→    if (lastLeg == null) {\n   123→      return LocalDateTime.MAX;\n   124→    } else {\n   125→      return lastLeg.getUnloadTime();\n   126→    }\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  /** @return The last leg on the itinerary. */\n   130→  Leg getLastLeg() {\n   131→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n   132→      return null;\n   133→    } else {\n   134→      return legs.get(legs.size() - 1);\n   135→    }\n   136→  }\n   137→\n   138→  private boolean sameValueAs(Itinerary other) {\n   139→    return other != null && legs.equals(other.legs);\n   140→  }\n   141→\n   142→  @Override\n   143→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   144→    if (this == o) {\n   145→      return true;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Itinerary)) {\n   149→      return false;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    Itinerary itinerary = (Itinerary) o;\n   153→\n   154→    return sameValueAs(itinerary);\n   155→  }\n   156→\n   157→  @Override\n   158→  public int hashCode() {\n   159→    return legs.hashCode();\n   160→  }\n   161→\n   162→  @Override\n   163→  public String toString() {\n   164→    return \"Itinerary{\" + \"legs=\" + legs + '}';\n   165→  }\n   166→}\n   167→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"93d9941f-c01c-4d59-819b-c79884cf248d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017HFNjxrvwkxGb2Nm6e96Hg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     9→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    10→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    11→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    15→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    18→\n    19→@Entity\n    20→public class Leg implements Serializable {\n    21→\n    22→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→\n    24→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    25→\n    26→  @ManyToOne\n    27→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    28→  @NotNull\n    29→  private Voyage voyage;\n    30→\n    31→  @ManyToOne\n    32→  @JoinColumn(name = \"load_location_id\")\n    33→  @NotNull\n    34→  private Location loadLocation;\n    35→\n    36→  @ManyToOne\n    37→  @JoinColumn(name = \"unload_location_id\")\n    38→  @NotNull\n    39→  private Location unloadLocation;\n    40→\n    41→  @Column(name = \"load_time\")\n    42→  @NotNull\n    43→  private LocalDateTime loadTime;\n    44→\n    45→  @Column(name = \"unload_time\")\n    46→  @NotNull\n    47→  private LocalDateTime unloadTime;\n    48→\n    49→  public Leg() {\n    50→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public Leg(\n    54→      Voyage voyage,\n    55→      Location loadLocation,\n    56→      Location unloadLocation,\n    57→      LocalDateTime loadTime,\n    58→      LocalDateTime unloadTime) {\n    59→    Validate.noNullElements(\n    60→        new Object[] {voyage, loadLocation, unloadLocation, loadTime, unloadTime});\n    61→\n    62→    this.voyage = voyage;\n    63→    this.loadLocation = loadLocation;\n    64→    this.unloadLocation = unloadLocation;\n    65→\n    66→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n    67→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n    68→    this.loadTime = loadTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    69→    this.unloadTime = unloadTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n    73→    return voyage;\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  public Location getLoadLocation() {\n    77→    return loadLocation;\n    78→  }\n    79→\n    80→  public Location getUnloadLocation() {\n    81→    return unloadLocation;\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  public LocalDateTime getLoadTime() {\n    85→    return this.loadTime;\n    86→  }\n    87→\n    88→  public LocalDateTime getUnloadTime() {\n    89→    return this.unloadTime;\n    90→  }\n    91→\n    92→  private boolean sameValueAs(Leg other) {\n    93→    return other != null\n    94→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n    95→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n    96→            .append(this.loadLocation, other.loadLocation)\n    97→            .append(this.unloadLocation, other.unloadLocation)\n    98→            .append(this.loadTime, other.loadTime)\n    99→            .append(this.unloadTime, other.unloadTime)\n   100→            .isEquals();\n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  @Override\n   104→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   105→    if (this == o) {\n   106→      return true;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Leg)) {\n   110→      return false;\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    Leg leg = (Leg) o;\n   114→\n   115→    return sameValueAs(leg);\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  @Override\n   119→  public int hashCode() {\n   120→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   121→        .append(voyage)\n   122→        .append(loadLocation)\n   123→        .append(unloadLocation)\n   124→        .append(loadTime)\n   125→        .append(unloadTime)\n   126→        .toHashCode();\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  @Override\n   130→  public String toString() {\n   131→    return \"Leg{\"\n   132→        + \"id=\"\n   133→        + id\n   134→        + \", voyage=\"\n   135→        + voyage\n   136→        + \", loadLocation=\"\n   137→        + loadLocation\n   138→        + \", unloadLocation=\"\n   139→        + unloadLocation\n   140→        + \", loadTime=\"\n   141→        + loadTime\n   142→        + \", unloadTime=\"\n   143→        + unloadTime\n   144→        + '}';\n   145→  }\n   146→}\n   147→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"8978740b-adcf-4499-8858-5608eec8f2b6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E4zzejMzBpwJXNdH1XA7Wm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     7→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     8→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n     9→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    10→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    11→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.AbstractSpecification;\n    15→\n    16→/**\n    17→ * Route specification. Describes where a cargo origin and destination is, and the arrival deadline.\n    18→ */\n    19→@Embeddable\n    20→public class RouteSpecification extends AbstractSpecification<Itinerary> implements Serializable {\n    21→\n    22→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→\n    24→  @ManyToOne\n    25→  @JoinColumn(name = \"spec_origin_id\", updatable = false)\n    26→  private Location origin;\n    27→\n    28→  @ManyToOne\n    29→  @JoinColumn(name = \"spec_destination_id\")\n    30→  private Location destination;\n    31→\n    32→  @Column(name = \"spec_arrival_deadline\")\n    33→  @NotNull\n    34→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    35→\n    36→  public RouteSpecification() {}\n    37→\n    38→  /**\n    39→   * @param origin origin location - can't be the same as the destination\n    40→   * @param destination destination location - can't be the same as the origin\n    41→   * @param arrivalDeadline arrival deadline\n    42→   */\n    43→  public RouteSpecification(Location origin, Location destination, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    44→    Validate.notNull(origin, \"Origin is required\");\n    45→    Validate.notNull(destination, \"Destination is required\");\n    46→    Validate.notNull(arrivalDeadline, \"Arrival deadline is required\");\n    47→    Validate.isTrue(\n    48→        !origin.sameIdentityAs(destination), \"Origin and destination can't be the same: \" + origin);\n    49→\n    50→    this.origin = origin;\n    51→    this.destination = destination;\n    52→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public Location getOrigin() {\n    56→    return origin;\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  public Location getDestination() {\n    60→    return destination;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n    64→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Override\n    68→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(Itinerary itinerary) {\n    69→    return itinerary != null\n    70→        && getOrigin().sameIdentityAs(itinerary.getInitialDepartureLocation())\n    71→        && getDestination().sameIdentityAs(itinerary.getFinalArrivalLocation())\n    72→        && getArrivalDeadline().isAfter(itinerary.getFinalArrivalDate().toLocalDate());\n    73→  }\n    74→\n    75→  private boolean sameValueAs(RouteSpecification other) {\n    76→    return other != null\n    77→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n    78→            .append(this.origin, other.origin)\n    79→            .append(this.destination, other.destination)\n    80→            .append(this.arrivalDeadline, other.arrivalDeadline)\n    81→            .isEquals();\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  @Override\n    85→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    86→    if (this == o) {\n    87→      return true;\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof RouteSpecification)) {\n    91→      return false;\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    RouteSpecification that = (RouteSpecification) o;\n    95→\n    96→    return sameValueAs(that);\n    97→  }\n    98→\n    99→  @Override\n   100→  public int hashCode() {\n   101→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   102→        .append(this.origin)\n   103→        .append(this.destination)\n   104→        .append(this.arrivalDeadline)\n   105→        .toHashCode();\n   106→  }\n   107→}\n   108→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"f655b0ea-84e0-476f-aef1-1d139e548035"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014yQnyFrfZUuBfXFfyR1mdV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     7→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n     8→\n     9→/** Uniquely identifies a particular cargo. Automatically generated by the application. */\n    10→@Embeddable\n    11→public class TrackingId implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  @Column(name = \"tracking_id\", unique = true, updatable = false)\n    16→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Tracking ID cannot be empty.\")\n    17→  private String id;\n    18→\n    19→  public TrackingId() {}\n    20→\n    21→  public TrackingId(String id) {\n    22→    Validate.notNull(id);\n    23→    this.id = id;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  public String getIdString() {\n    27→    return id;\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    32→    if (this == o) {\n    33→      return true;\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof TrackingId)) {\n    37→      return false;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    TrackingId other = (TrackingId) o;\n    41→\n    42→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  public int hashCode() {\n    47→    return id.hashCode();\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  boolean sameValueAs(TrackingId other) {\n    51→    return other != null && this.id.equals(other.id);\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public String toString() {\n    56→    return id;\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"a36aba99-3b18-439a-8b14-a141cf413ce8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CznMvsPUfckkYyk2XdFe48","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import javax.persistence.EnumType;\n     9→import javax.persistence.Enumerated;\n    10→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    11→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    12→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    13→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    14→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    15→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    16→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    17→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    18→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    19→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    25→\n    26→/**\n    27→ * A HandlingEvent is used to register the event when, for instance, a cargo is unloaded from a\n    28→ * carrier at a some location at a given time.\n    29→ *\n    30→ * <p>The HandlingEvent's are sent from different Incident Logging Applications some time after the\n    31→ * event occurred and contain information about the null {@link TrackingId}, {@link Location}, time\n    32→ * stamp of the completion of the event, and possibly, if applicable a {@link Voyage}.\n    33→ *\n    34→ * <p>This class is the only member, and consequently the root, of the HandlingEvent aggregate.\n    35→ *\n    36→ * <p>HandlingEvent's could contain information about a {@link Voyage} and if so, the event type\n    37→ * must be either {@link Type#LOAD} or {@link Type#UNLOAD}.\n    38→ *\n    39→ * <p>All other events must be of {@link Type#RECEIVE}, {@link Type#CLAIM} or {@link Type#CUSTOMS}.\n    40→ */\n    41→@Entity\n    42→@NamedQuery(\n    43→    name = \"HandlingEvent.findByTrackingId\",\n    44→    query = \"Select e from HandlingEvent e where e.cargo.trackingId = :trackingId\")\n    45→public class HandlingEvent implements Serializable {\n    46→\n    47→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    48→\n    49→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    50→\n    51→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    52→  @NotNull\n    53→  private Type type;\n    54→\n    55→  @ManyToOne\n    56→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    57→  private Voyage voyage;\n    58→\n    59→  @ManyToOne\n    60→  @JoinColumn(name = \"location_id\")\n    61→  @NotNull\n    62→  private Location location;\n    63→\n    64→  @NotNull\n    65→  @Column(name = \"completionTime\")\n    66→  private LocalDateTime completionTime;\n    67→\n    68→  @NotNull\n    69→  @Column(name = \"registration\")\n    70→  private LocalDateTime registrationTime;\n    71→\n    72→  @ManyToOne\n    73→  @JoinColumn(name = \"cargo_id\")\n    74→  @NotNull\n    75→  private Cargo cargo;\n    76→\n    77→  @Transient private String summary;\n    78→\n    79→  public HandlingEvent() {\n    80→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  /**\n    84→   * @param cargo The cargo\n    85→   * @param completionTime completion time, the reported time that the event actually happened (e.g.\n    86→   *     the receive took place).\n    87→   * @param registrationTime registration time, the time the message is received\n    88→   * @param type type of event\n    89→   * @param location where the event took place\n    90→   * @param voyage the voyage\n    91→   */\n    92→  public HandlingEvent(\n    93→      Cargo cargo,\n    94→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    95→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n    96→      Type type,\n    97→      Location location,\n    98→      Voyage voyage) {\n    99→    Validate.notNull(cargo, \"Cargo is required\");\n   100→    Validate.notNull(completionTime, \"Completion time is required\");\n   101→    Validate.notNull(registrationTime, \"Registration time is required\");\n   102→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n   103→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n   104→    Validate.notNull(voyage, \"Voyage is required\");\n   105→\n   106→    if (type.prohibitsVoyage()) {\n   107→      throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Voyage is not allowed with event type \" + type);\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    this.voyage = voyage;\n   111→\n   112→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   113→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   114→    this.completionTime = completionTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   115→    this.registrationTime = registrationTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   116→    this.type = type;\n   117→    this.location = location;\n   118→    this.cargo = cargo;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  /**\n   122→   * @param cargo cargo\n   123→   * @param completionTime completion time, the reported time that the event actually happened (e.g.\n   124→   *     the receive took place).\n   125→   * @param registrationTime registration time, the time the message is received\n   126→   * @param type type of event\n   127→   * @param location where the event took place\n   128→   */\n   129→  public HandlingEvent(\n   130→      Cargo cargo,\n   131→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n   132→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n   133→      Type type,\n   134→      Location location) {\n   135→    Validate.notNull(cargo, \"Cargo is required\");\n   136→    Validate.notNull(completionTime, \"Completion time is required\");\n   137→    Validate.notNull(registrationTime, \"Registration time is required\");\n   138→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n   139→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n   140→\n   141→    if (type.requiresVoyage()) {\n   142→      throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Voyage is required for event type \" + type);\n   143→    }\n   144→\n   145→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   146→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   147→    this.completionTime = completionTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   148→    this.registrationTime = registrationTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   149→    this.type = type;\n   150→    this.location = location;\n   151→    this.cargo = cargo;\n   152→    this.voyage = null;\n   153→  }\n   154→\n   155→  public Type getType() {\n   156→    return this.type;\n   157→  }\n   158→\n   159→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n   160→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(this.voyage, Voyage.NONE);\n   161→  }\n   162→\n   163→  public LocalDateTime getCompletionTime() {\n   164→    return completionTime;\n   165→  }\n   166→\n   167→  public LocalDateTime getRegistrationTime() {\n   168→    return registrationTime;\n   169→  }\n   170→\n   171→  public Location getLocation() {\n   172→    return this.location;\n   173→  }\n   174→\n   175→  public Cargo getCargo() {\n   176→    return this.cargo;\n   177→  }\n   178→\n   179→  public String getSummary() {\n   180→    StringBuilder builder =\n   181→        new StringBuilder(location.getName())\n   182→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   183→            .append(completionTime)\n   184→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   185→            .append(\"Type: \")\n   186→            .append(type)\n   187→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   188→            .append(\"Reg.: \")\n   189→            .append(registrationTime)\n   190→            .append(\"\\n\");\n   191→\n   192→    if (voyage != null) {\n   193→      builder.append(\"Voyage: \").append(voyage.getVoyageNumber());\n   194→    }\n   195→\n   196→    return builder.toString();\n   197→  }\n   198→\n   199→  @Override\n   200→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   201→    if (this == o) {\n   202→      return true;\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof HandlingEvent)) {\n   206→      return false;\n   207→    }\n   208→\n   209→    HandlingEvent event = (HandlingEvent) o;\n   210→\n   211→    return sameEventAs(event);\n   212→  }\n   213→\n   214→  private boolean sameEventAs(HandlingEvent other) {\n   215→    return other != null\n   216→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   217→            .append(this.cargo, other.cargo)\n   218→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n   219→            .append(this.completionTime, other.completionTime)\n   220→            .append(this.location, other.location)\n   221→            .append(this.type, other.type)\n   222→            .isEquals();\n   223→  }\n   224→\n   225→  @Override\n   226→  public int hashCode() {\n   227→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   228→        .append(cargo)\n   229→        .append(voyage)\n   230→        .append(completionTime)\n   231→        .append(location)\n   232→        .append(type)\n   233→        .toHashCode();\n   234→  }\n   235→\n   236→  @Override\n   237→  public String toString() {\n   238→    StringBuilder builder =\n   239→        new StringBuilder(\"\\n--- Handling event ---\\n\")\n   240→            .append(\"Cargo: \")\n   241→            .append(cargo.getTrackingId())\n   242→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   243→            .append(\"Type: \")\n   244→            .append(type)\n   245→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   246→            .append(\"Location: \")\n   247→            .append(location.getName())\n   248→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   249→            .append(\"Completed on: \")\n   250→            .append(completionTime)\n   251→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   252→            .append(\"Registered on: \")\n   253→            .append(registrationTime)\n   254→            .append(\"\\n\");\n   255→\n   256→    if (voyage != null) {\n   257→      builder.append(\"Voyage: \").append(voyage.getVoyageNumber()).append(\"\\n\");\n   258→    }\n   259→\n   260→    return builder.toString();\n   261→  }\n   262→\n   263→  /**\n   264→   * Handling event type. Either requires or prohibits a carrier movement association, it's never\n   265→   * optional.\n   266→   */\n   267→  public enum Type {\n   268→\n   269→    // Loaded onto voyage from port location.\n   270→    LOAD(true),\n   271→    // Unloaded from voyage to port location\n   272→    UNLOAD(true),\n   273→    // Received by carrier\n   274→    RECEIVE(false),\n   275→    // Cargo claimed by recepient\n   276→    CLAIM(false),\n   277→    // Cargo went through customs\n   278→    CUSTOMS(false);\n   279→\n   280→    private final boolean voyageRequired;\n   281→\n   282→    /**\n   283→     * Private enum constructor.\n   284→     *\n   285→     * @param voyageRequired whether or not a voyage is associated with this event type\n   286→     */\n   287→    private Type(boolean voyageRequired) {\n   288→      this.voyageRequired = voyageRequired;\n   289→    }\n   290→\n   291→    /** @return True if a voyage association is required for this event type. */\n   292→    public boolean requiresVoyage() {\n   293→      return voyageRequired;\n   294→    }\n   295→\n   296→    /** @return True if a voyage association is prohibited for this event type. */\n   297→    public boolean prohibitsVoyage() {\n   298→      return !requiresVoyage();\n   299→    }\n   300→\n   301→    public boolean sameValueAs(Type other) {\n   302→      return other != null && this.equals(other);\n   303→    }\n   304→  }\n   305→}\n   306→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"8542ad77-b4cc-4e65-86a5-75546008ce08"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDJDRmehipA2cWWjkJpDb2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class HandlingEventFactory implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    23→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    24→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    25→\n    26→  /**\n    27→   * @param registrationTime time when this event was received by the system\n    28→   * @param completionTime when the event was completed, for example finished loading\n    29→   * @param trackingId cargo tracking id\n    30→   * @param voyageNumber voyage number\n    31→   * @param unlocode United Nations Location Code for the location of the event\n    32→   * @param type type of event\n    33→   * @return A handling event.\n    34→   * @throws UnknownVoyageException if there's no voyage with this number\n    35→   * @throws UnknownCargoException if there's no cargo with this tracking id\n    36→   * @throws UnknownLocationException if there's no location with this UN Locode\n    37→   */\n    38→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look at the exception handling more seriously.\n    39→  public HandlingEvent createHandlingEvent(\n    40→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n    41→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    42→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    43→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    44→      UnLocode unlocode,\n    45→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    46→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    47→    Cargo cargo = findCargo(trackingId);\n    48→    Voyage voyage = findVoyage(voyageNumber);\n    49→    Location location = findLocation(unlocode);\n    50→\n    51→    try {\n    52→      if (voyage == null) {\n    53→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location);\n    54→      } else {\n    55→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location, voyage);\n    56→      }\n    57→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    58→      throw new CannotCreateHandlingEventException(e);\n    59→    }\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  private Cargo findCargo(TrackingId trackingId) throws UnknownCargoException {\n    63→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    64→\n    65→    if (cargo == null) {\n    66→      throw new UnknownCargoException(trackingId);\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    return cargo;\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  private Voyage findVoyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) throws UnknownVoyageException {\n    73→    if (voyageNumber == null) {\n    74→      return null;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    Voyage voyage = voyageRepository.find(voyageNumber);\n    78→\n    79→    if (voyage == null) {\n    80→      throw new UnknownVoyageException(voyageNumber);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    return voyage;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  private Location findLocation(UnLocode unlocode) throws UnknownLocationException {\n    87→    Location location = locationRepository.find(unlocode);\n    88→\n    89→    if (location == null) {\n    90→      throw new UnknownLocationException(unlocode);\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    return location;\n    94→  }\n    95→}\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"418dc040-f31b-4a32-8502-2f2d73ac8d84"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018Bkm49nE41KKXU5ZKtjvcm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.Collection;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.Comparator;\n     7→import java.util.HashSet;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    10→\n    11→public class HandlingHistory {\n    12→\n    13→  // Null object pattern.\n    14→  public static final HandlingHistory EMPTY =\n    15→      new HandlingHistory(Collections.<HandlingEvent>emptyList());\n    16→  private static final Comparator<HandlingEvent> BY_COMPLETION_TIME_COMPARATOR =\n    17→      Comparator.comparing(HandlingEvent::getCompletionTime);\n    18→\n    19→  private final List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents;\n    20→\n    21→  public HandlingHistory(Collection<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents) {\n    22→    Validate.notNull(handlingEvents, \"Handling events are required.\");\n    23→\n    24→    this.handlingEvents = new ArrayList<>(handlingEvents);\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public List<HandlingEvent> getAllHandlingEvents() {\n    28→    return handlingEvents;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  /**\n    32→   * @return A distinct list (no duplicate registrations) of handling events, ordered by completion\n    33→   *     time.\n    34→   */\n    35→  public List<HandlingEvent> getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime() {\n    36→    List<HandlingEvent> ordered = new ArrayList<>(new HashSet<>(handlingEvents));\n    37→    ordered.sort(BY_COMPLETION_TIME_COMPARATOR);\n    38→\n    39→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(ordered);\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  /** @return Most recently completed event, or null if the delivery history is empty. */\n    43→  public HandlingEvent getMostRecentlyCompletedEvent() {\n    44→    List<HandlingEvent> distinctEvents = getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n    45→\n    46→    if (distinctEvents.isEmpty()) {\n    47→      return null;\n    48→    } else {\n    49→      return distinctEvents.get(distinctEvents.size() - 1);\n    50→    }\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  private boolean sameValueAs(HandlingHistory other) {\n    54→    return other != null && this.handlingEvents.equals(other.handlingEvents);\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  @Override\n    58→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    59→    if (this == o) {\n    60→      return true;\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof HandlingHistory)) {\n    64→      return false;\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    HandlingHistory other = (HandlingHistory) o;\n    68→\n    69→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  @Override\n    73→  public int hashCode() {\n    74→    return handlingEvents.hashCode();\n    75→  }\n    76→}\n    77→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"de32fca2-7c01-4a06-8393-bea197f75257"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0179cCxRammRFHjayU9nHWMb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     6→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Id;\n     8→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n     9→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    10→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    11→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * A location in our model is stops on a journey, such as cargo origin or destination, or carrier\n    15→ * movement end points.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>It is uniquely identified by a UN location code.\n    18→ */\n    19→@Entity\n    20→@NamedQuery(name = \"Location.findAll\", query = \"Select l from Location l\")\n    21→@NamedQuery(\n    22→    name = \"Location.findByUnLocode\",\n    23→    query = \"Select l from Location l where l.unLocode = :unLocode\")\n    24→public class Location implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  // Special Location object that marks an unknown location.\n    29→  public static final Location UNKNOWN = new Location(new UnLocode(\"XXXXX\"), \"Unknown location\");\n    30→\n    31→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    32→  @Embedded @NotNull private UnLocode unLocode;\n    33→  @NotEmpty private String name;\n    34→\n    35→  public Location() {\n    36→    // Nothing to do.\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  /**\n    40→   * @param unLocode UN Locode\n    41→   * @param name Location name\n    42→   * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the UN Locode or name is null\n    43→   */\n    44→  public Location(UnLocode unLocode, String name) {\n    45→    Validate.notNull(unLocode);\n    46→    Validate.notNull(name);\n    47→\n    48→    this.unLocode = unLocode;\n    49→    this.name = name;\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  /** @return UN location code for this location. */\n    53→  public UnLocode getUnLocode() {\n    54→    return unLocode;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  /** @return Actual name of this location, e.g. \"Stockholm\". */\n    58→  public String getName() {\n    59→    return name;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  /**\n    63→   * @param object to compare\n    64→   * @return Since this is an entiy this will be true iff UN locodes are equal.\n    65→   */\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public boolean equals(Object object) {\n    68→    if (object == null) {\n    69→      return false;\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    if (this == object) {\n    73→      return true;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    if (!(object instanceof Location)) {\n    77→      return false;\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    Location other = (Location) object;\n    81→\n    82→    return sameIdentityAs(other);\n    83→  }\n    84→\n    85→  public boolean sameIdentityAs(Location other) {\n    86→    return this.unLocode.sameValueAs(other.unLocode);\n    87→  }\n    88→\n    89→  /** @return Hash code of UN locode. */\n    90→  @Override\n    91→  public int hashCode() {\n    92→    return unLocode.hashCode();\n    93→  }\n    94→\n    95→  @Override\n    96→  public String toString() {\n    97→    return name + \" [\" + unLocode + \"]\";\n    98→  }\n    99→}\n   100→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"2d01e554-0787-450d-bb43-bbb6f67053f1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013csNTtTGQcQGH8wiYZAJE1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n     8→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     9→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    10→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    11→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    15→\n    16→@Entity\n    17→@NamedQuery(\n    18→    name = \"Voyage.findByVoyageNumber\",\n    19→    query = \"Select v from Voyage v where v.voyageNumber = :voyageNumber\")\n    20→@NamedQuery(name = \"Voyage.findAll\", query = \"Select v from Voyage v order by v.voyageNumber\")\n    21→public class Voyage implements Serializable {\n    22→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→\n    24→  // Null object pattern\n    25→  public static final Voyage NONE = new Voyage(new VoyageNumber(\"\"), Schedule.EMPTY);\n    26→\n    27→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    28→\n    29→  @Embedded\n    30→  @NotNull(message = \"Voyage number is required.\")\n    31→  private VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    32→\n    33→  @Embedded\n    34→  @NotNull(message = \"Schedule is required.\")\n    35→  private Schedule schedule;\n    36→\n    37→  public Voyage() {\n    38→    // Nothing to initialize\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public Voyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber, Schedule schedule) {\n    42→    Validate.notNull(voyageNumber, \"Voyage number is required.\");\n    43→    Validate.notNull(schedule, \"Schedule is required.\");\n    44→\n    45→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    46→    this.schedule = schedule;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public VoyageNumber getVoyageNumber() {\n    50→    return voyageNumber;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public Schedule getSchedule() {\n    54→    return schedule;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  @Override\n    58→  public int hashCode() {\n    59→    return voyageNumber.hashCode();\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  @Override\n    63→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    64→    if (this == o) {\n    65→      return true;\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    if (o == null) {\n    69→      return false;\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    if (!(o instanceof Voyage)) {\n    73→      return false;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    Voyage that = (Voyage) o;\n    77→\n    78→    return sameIdentityAs(that);\n    79→  }\n    80→\n    81→  public boolean sameIdentityAs(Voyage other) {\n    82→    return other != null && this.getVoyageNumber().sameValueAs(other.getVoyageNumber());\n    83→  }\n    84→\n    85→  @Override\n    86→  public String toString() {\n    87→    return \"Voyage \" + voyageNumber;\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  /**\n    91→   * Builder pattern is used for incremental construction of a Voyage aggregate. This serves as an\n    92→   * aggregate factory.\n    93→   */\n    94→  public static class Builder {\n    95→\n    96→    private List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements = new ArrayList<>();\n    97→    private VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    98→    private Location departureLocation;\n    99→\n   100→    public Builder(VoyageNumber voyageNumber, Location departureLocation) {\n   101→      Validate.notNull(voyageNumber, \"Voyage number is required\");\n   102→      Validate.notNull(departureLocation, \"Departure location is required\");\n   103→\n   104→      this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n   105→      this.departureLocation = departureLocation;\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    public Builder addMovement(\n   109→        Location arrivalLocation, LocalDateTime departureTime, LocalDateTime arrivalTime) {\n   110→      carrierMovements.add(\n   111→          new CarrierMovement(departureLocation, arrivalLocation, departureTime, arrivalTime));\n   112→\n   113→      // Next departure location is the same as this arrival location\n   114→      this.departureLocation = arrivalLocation;\n   115→\n   116→      return this;\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    public Voyage build() {\n   120→      return new Voyage(voyageNumber, new Schedule(carrierMovements));\n   121→    }\n   122→  }\n   123→}\n   124→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"d6f0f1ba-b77e-4f94-b5ba-1a4c32ba383c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B8MApyFvgwdPzyNqusaA9G","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     9→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    10→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    11→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    12→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    13→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    15→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    16→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    18→\n    19→/** A carrier movement is a vessel voyage from one location to another. */\n    20→@Entity\n    21→@Table(name = \"carrier_movement\")\n    22→public class CarrierMovement implements Serializable {\n    23→\n    24→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    25→\n    26→  // Null object pattern\n    27→  public static final CarrierMovement NONE =\n    28→      new CarrierMovement(Location.UNKNOWN, Location.UNKNOWN, LocalDateTime.MIN, LocalDateTime.MIN);\n    29→\n    30→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    31→\n    32→  @ManyToOne\n    33→  @JoinColumn(name = \"departure_location_id\")\n    34→  @NotNull\n    35→  private Location departureLocation;\n    36→\n    37→  @ManyToOne\n    38→  @JoinColumn(name = \"arrival_location_id\")\n    39→  @NotNull\n    40→  private Location arrivalLocation;\n    41→\n    42→  @Column(name = \"departure_time\")\n    43→  @NotNull\n    44→  private LocalDateTime departureTime;\n    45→\n    46→  @Column(name = \"arrival_time\")\n    47→  @NotNull\n    48→  private LocalDateTime arrivalTime;\n    49→\n    50→  public CarrierMovement() {\n    51→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public CarrierMovement(\n    55→      Location departureLocation,\n    56→      Location arrivalLocation,\n    57→      LocalDateTime departureTime,\n    58→      LocalDateTime arrivalTime) {\n    59→    Validate.noNullElements(\n    60→        new Object[] {departureLocation, arrivalLocation, departureTime, arrivalTime});\n    61→\n    62→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n    63→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n    64→    this.departureTime = departureTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    65→    this.arrivalTime = arrivalTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    66→    this.departureLocation = departureLocation;\n    67→    this.arrivalLocation = arrivalLocation;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public Location getDepartureLocation() {\n    71→    return departureLocation;\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  public Location getArrivalLocation() {\n    75→    return arrivalLocation;\n    76→  }\n    77→\n    78→  public LocalDateTime getDepartureTime() {\n    79→    return departureTime;\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public LocalDateTime getArrivalTime() {\n    83→    return arrivalTime;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  @Override\n    87→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    88→    if (this == o) {\n    89→      return true;\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof CarrierMovement)) {\n    93→      return false;\n    94→    }\n    95→\n    96→    CarrierMovement that = (CarrierMovement) o;\n    97→\n    98→    return sameValueAs(that);\n    99→  }\n   100→\n   101→  @Override\n   102→  public int hashCode() {\n   103→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   104→        .append(this.departureLocation)\n   105→        .append(this.departureTime)\n   106→        .append(this.arrivalLocation)\n   107→        .append(this.arrivalTime)\n   108→        .toHashCode();\n   109→  }\n   110→\n   111→  private boolean sameValueAs(CarrierMovement other) {\n   112→    return other != null\n   113→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   114→            .append(this.departureLocation, other.departureLocation)\n   115→            .append(this.departureTime, other.departureTime)\n   116→            .append(this.arrivalLocation, other.arrivalLocation)\n   117→            .append(this.arrivalTime, other.arrivalTime)\n   118→            .isEquals();\n   119→  }\n   120→}\n   121→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"fc9a6678-b69a-41bc-b2d0-e99478ead6d8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019se1HQdUrMPn8Y1KFydWrQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.persistence.CascadeType;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     8→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\n    10→import javax.persistence.OrderColumn;\n    11→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    15→\n    16→/** A voyage schedule. */\n    17→@Embeddable\n    18→public class Schedule implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    21→\n    22→  // Null object pattern.\n    23→  public static final Schedule EMPTY = new Schedule();\n    24→\n    25→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look into why cascade delete doesn't work.\n    26→  @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL)\n    27→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    28→  @OrderColumn(name = \"movement_order\")\n    29→  @NotNull\n    30→  @Size(min = 1)\n    31→  private List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements = Collections.emptyList();\n    32→\n    33→  public Schedule() {\n    34→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  Schedule(List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements) {\n    38→    Validate.notNull(carrierMovements);\n    39→    Validate.noNullElements(carrierMovements);\n    40→    Validate.notEmpty(carrierMovements);\n    41→\n    42→    this.carrierMovements = carrierMovements;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public List<CarrierMovement> getCarrierMovements() {\n    46→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(carrierMovements);\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  private boolean sameValueAs(Schedule other) {\n    50→    return other != null && this.carrierMovements.equals(other.carrierMovements);\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @Override\n    54→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    55→    if (this == o) {\n    56→      return true;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Schedule)) {\n    60→      return false;\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    Schedule that = (Schedule) o;\n    64→\n    65→    return sameValueAs(that);\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public int hashCode() {\n    70→    return new HashCodeBuilder().append(this.carrierMovements).toHashCode();\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"146bdb3d-f5a2-4085-a425-c41b64721388"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhfHhu9PD8rodfZxBxDnFe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.lang.reflect.Field;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collections;\n     7→import java.util.HashMap;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import java.util.Map;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations;\n    12→\n    13→/** Sample carrier movements, for demo/test purposes. */\n    14→public class SampleVoyages {\n    15→\n    16→  public static final Voyage CM001 =\n    17→      createVoyage(\"CM001\", SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM, SampleLocations.HAMBURG);\n    18→  public static final Voyage CM002 =\n    19→      createVoyage(\"CM002\", SampleLocations.HAMBURG, SampleLocations.HONGKONG);\n    20→  public static final Voyage CM003 =\n    21→      createVoyage(\"CM003\", SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.NEWYORK);\n    22→  public static final Voyage CM004 =\n    23→      createVoyage(\"CM004\", SampleLocations.NEWYORK, SampleLocations.CHICAGO);\n    24→  public static final Voyage CM005 =\n    25→      createVoyage(\"CM005\", SampleLocations.CHICAGO, SampleLocations.HAMBURG);\n    26→  public static final Voyage CM006 =\n    27→      createVoyage(\"CM006\", SampleLocations.HAMBURG, SampleLocations.HANGZOU);\n    28→  public static final Voyage v100 =\n    29→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V100\"), SampleLocations.HONGKONG)\n    30→          .addMovement(\n    31→              SampleLocations.TOKYO,\n    32→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(3).plusHours(6),\n    33→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(5).plusHours(18))\n    34→          .addMovement(\n    35→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n    36→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(6).plusHours(11),\n    37→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(9).plusHours(11))\n    38→          .build();\n    39→  public static final Voyage v200 =\n    40→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V200\"), SampleLocations.TOKYO)\n    41→          .addMovement(\n    42→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n    43→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(6).plusHours(14),\n    44→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(8).plusHours(7))\n    45→          .addMovement(\n    46→              SampleLocations.CHICAGO,\n    47→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(10).plusHours(21),\n    48→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(2))\n    49→          .addMovement(\n    50→              SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n    51→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(1),\n    52→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(16).plusHours(23))\n    53→          .build();\n    54→  public static final Voyage v300 =\n    55→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V300\"), SampleLocations.TOKYO)\n    56→          .addMovement(\n    57→              SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM,\n    58→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(8).plusHours(8),\n    59→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(11).plusHours(16))\n    60→          .addMovement(\n    61→              SampleLocations.HAMBURG,\n    62→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(11).plusHours(4),\n    63→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(12).plusHours(17))\n    64→          .addMovement(\n    65→              SampleLocations.MELBOURNE,\n    66→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(9),\n    67→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(18).plusHours(10))\n    68→          .addMovement(\n    69→              SampleLocations.TOKYO,\n    70→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(19).plusHours(17),\n    71→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(21).plusHours(4))\n    72→          .build();\n    73→  public static final Voyage v400 =\n    74→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V400\"), SampleLocations.HAMBURG)\n    75→          .addMovement(\n    76→              SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n    77→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(9),\n    78→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(15).plusHours(18))\n    79→          .addMovement(\n    80→              SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n    81→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(15).plusHours(11),\n    82→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(16).plusHours(16))\n    83→          .addMovement(\n    84→              SampleLocations.HAMBURG,\n    85→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(20).plusHours(18),\n    86→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(22).plusHours(9))\n    87→          .build();\n    88→  /**\n    89→   * Voyage number 0100S (by ship)\n    90→   *\n    91→   * <p>Hongkong - Hangzou - Tokyo - Melbourne - New York\n    92→   */\n    93→  public static final Voyage HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK =\n    94→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0100S\"), SampleLocations.HONGKONG)\n    95→          .addMovement(\n    96→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU,\n    97→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(1).plusHours(12),\n    98→              LocalDateTime.now()\n    99→                  .minusYears(1)\n   100→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   101→                  .plusDays(3)\n   102→                  .plusHours(14)\n   103→                  .plusMinutes(30))\n   104→          .addMovement(\n   105→              SampleLocations.TOKYO,\n   106→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(4).plusHours(21),\n   107→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   108→                  .minusYears(1)\n   109→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   110→                  .plusDays(6)\n   111→                  .plusHours(6)\n   112→                  .plusMinutes(15))\n   113→          .addMovement(\n   114→              SampleLocations.MELBOURNE,\n   115→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(9).plusHours(11),\n   116→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   117→                  .minusYears(1)\n   118→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   119→                  .plusDays(12)\n   120→                  .plusHours(11)\n   121→                  .plusMinutes(30))\n   122→          .addMovement(\n   123→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   124→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(14).plusHours(12),\n   125→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   126→                  .minusYears(1)\n   127→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   128→                  .plusDays(23)\n   129→                  .plusHours(23)\n   130→                  .plusMinutes(10))\n   131→          .build();\n   132→  /**\n   133→   * Voyage number 0200T (by train)\n   134→   *\n   135→   * <p>New York - Chicago - Dallas\n   136→   */\n   137→  public static final Voyage NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS =\n   138→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0200T\"), SampleLocations.NEWYORK)\n   139→          .addMovement(\n   140→              SampleLocations.CHICAGO,\n   141→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(24).plusHours(7),\n   142→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   143→                  .minusYears(1)\n   144→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   145→                  .plusDays(24)\n   146→                  .plusHours(17)\n   147→                  .plusMinutes(45))\n   148→          .addMovement(\n   149→              SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   150→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   151→                  .minusYears(1)\n   152→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   153→                  .plusDays(24)\n   154→                  .plusHours(21)\n   155→                  .plusMinutes(25),\n   156→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   157→                  .minusYears(1)\n   158→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   159→                  .plusDays(25)\n   160→                  .plusHours(19)\n   161→                  .plusMinutes(30))\n   162→          .build();\n   163→  /**\n   164→   * Voyage number 0300A (by airplane)\n   165→   *\n   166→   * <p>Dallas - Hamburg - Stockholm - Helsinki\n   167→   */\n   168→  public static final Voyage DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI =\n   169→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0300A\"), SampleLocations.DALLAS)\n   170→          .addMovement(\n   171→              SampleLocations.HAMBURG,\n   172→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   173→                  .minusYears(1)\n   174→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   175→                  .plusDays(29)\n   176→                  .plusHours(3)\n   177→                  .plusMinutes(30),\n   178→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(31).plusHours(14))\n   179→          .addMovement(\n   180→              SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n   181→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   182→                  .minusYears(1)\n   183→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   184→                  .plusDays(1)\n   185→                  .plusHours(15)\n   186→                  .plusMinutes(20),\n   187→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   188→                  .minusYears(1)\n   189→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   190→                  .plusDays(1)\n   191→                  .plusHours(18)\n   192→                  .plusMinutes(40))\n   193→          .addMovement(\n   194→              SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n   195→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(11).plusDays(2).plusHours(9),\n   196→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   197→                  .minusYears(1)\n   198→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   199→                  .plusDays(2)\n   200→                  .plusHours(11)\n   201→                  .plusMinutes(15))\n   202→          .build();\n   203→  /**\n   204→   * Voyage number 0301S (by ship)\n   205→   *\n   206→   * <p>Dallas - Hamburg - Stockholm - Helsinki, alternate route\n   207→   */\n   208→  public static final Voyage DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI_ALT =\n   209→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0301S\"), SampleLocations.DALLAS)\n   210→          .addMovement(\n   211→              SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n   212→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   213→                  .minusYears(1)\n   214→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   215→                  .plusDays(29)\n   216→                  .plusHours(3)\n   217→                  .plusMinutes(30),\n   218→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   219→                  .minusYears(1)\n   220→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   221→                  .plusDays(5)\n   222→                  .plusHours(15)\n   223→                  .plusMinutes(45))\n   224→          .build();\n   225→  /**\n   226→   * Voyage number 0400S (by ship)\n   227→   *\n   228→   * <p>Helsinki - Rotterdam - Shanghai - Hongkong\n   229→   */\n   230→  public static final Voyage HELSINKI_TO_HONGKONG =\n   231→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0400S\"), SampleLocations.HELSINKI)\n   232→          .addMovement(\n   233→              SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM,\n   234→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   235→                  .minusYears(1)\n   236→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   237→                  .plusDays(4)\n   238→                  .plusHours(5)\n   239→                  .plusMinutes(50),\n   240→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   241→                  .minusYears(1)\n   242→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   243→                  .plusDays(6)\n   244→                  .plusHours(14)\n   245→                  .plusMinutes(10))\n   246→          .addMovement(\n   247→              SampleLocations.SHANGHAI,\n   248→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   249→                  .minusYears(1)\n   250→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   251→                  .plusDays(10)\n   252→                  .plusHours(21)\n   253→                  .plusMinutes(45),\n   254→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   255→                  .minusYears(1)\n   256→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   257→                  .plusDays(22)\n   258→                  .plusHours(16)\n   259→                  .plusMinutes(40))\n   260→          .addMovement(\n   261→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG,\n   262→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(11).plusDays(24).plusHours(7),\n   263→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   264→                  .minusYears(1)\n   265→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   266→                  .plusDays(28)\n   267→                  .plusHours(13)\n   268→                  .plusMinutes(37))\n   269→          .build();\n   270→\n   271→  public static final Map<VoyageNumber, Voyage> ALL = new HashMap<>();\n   272→\n   273→  static {\n   274→    for (Field field : SampleVoyages.class.getDeclaredFields()) {\n   275→      if (field.getType().equals(Voyage.class)) {\n   276→        try {\n   277→          Voyage voyage = (Voyage) field.get(null);\n   278→          ALL.put(voyage.getVoyageNumber(), voyage);\n   279→        } catch (IllegalAccessException e) {\n   280→          throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   281→        }\n   282→      }\n   283→    }\n   284→  }\n   285→\n   286→  private static Voyage createVoyage(String id, Location from, Location to) {\n   287→    return new Voyage(\n   288→        new VoyageNumber(id),\n   289→        new Schedule(\n   290→            Collections.singletonList(\n   291→                new CarrierMovement(from, to, LocalDateTime.now(), LocalDateTime.now()))));\n   292→  }\n   293→\n   294→  public static List<Voyage> getAll() {\n   295→    return new ArrayList<>(ALL.values());\n   296→  }\n   297→\n   298→  public static Voyage lookup(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) {\n   299→    return ALL.get(voyageNumber);\n   300→  }\n   301→}\n   302→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"6f00e202-11a9-46f5-b409-72ebe0b957c9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019NuHeJnzHPUz8jNr7WeHnw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→/** Sample locations, for test purposes. */\n     4→public class SampleLocations {\n     5→\n     6→  public static final Location HONGKONG = new Location(new UnLocode(\"CNHKG\"), \"Hong Kong\");\n     7→  public static final Location MELBOURNE = new Location(new UnLocode(\"AUMEL\"), \"Melbourne\");\n     8→  public static final Location STOCKHOLM = new Location(new UnLocode(\"SESTO\"), \"Stockholm\");\n     9→  public static final Location HELSINKI = new Location(new UnLocode(\"FIHEL\"), \"Helsinki\");\n    10→  public static final Location CHICAGO = new Location(new UnLocode(\"USCHI\"), \"Chicago\");\n    11→  public static final Location TOKYO = new Location(new UnLocode(\"JNTKO\"), \"Tokyo\");\n    12→  public static final Location HAMBURG = new Location(new UnLocode(\"DEHAM\"), \"Hamburg\");\n    13→  public static final Location SHANGHAI = new Location(new UnLocode(\"CNSHA\"), \"Shanghai\");\n    14→  public static final Location ROTTERDAM = new Location(new UnLocode(\"NLRTM\"), \"Rotterdam\");\n    15→  public static final Location GOTHENBURG = new Location(new UnLocode(\"SEGOT\"), \"Gothenburg\");\n    16→  public static final Location HANGZOU = new Location(new UnLocode(\"CNHGH\"), \"Hangzhou\");\n    17→  public static final Location NEWYORK = new Location(new UnLocode(\"USNYC\"), \"New York\");\n    18→  public static final Location DALLAS = new Location(new UnLocode(\"USDAL\"), \"Dallas\");\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"699b95c0-a527-4659-9494-45152a6691a7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019HLDTYUC3UuaRVaSiNFVhM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.BookingService;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    25→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.CargoRouteDtoAssembler;\n    26→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.CargoStatusDtoAssembler;\n    27→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler;\n    28→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.LocationDtoAssembler;\n    29→\n    30→@ApplicationScoped\n    31→public class DefaultBookingServiceFacade implements BookingServiceFacade, Serializable {\n    32→\n    33→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    34→\n    35→  @Inject private BookingService bookingService;\n    36→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    37→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    38→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    39→  @Inject private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    40→  @Inject private CargoRouteDtoAssembler cargoRouteDtoAssembler;\n    41→  @Inject private CargoStatusDtoAssembler cargoStatusDtoAssembler;\n    42→  @Inject private ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler itineraryCandidateDtoAssembler;\n    43→  @Inject private LocationDtoAssembler locationDtoAssembler;\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  public List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location>\n    47→      listShippingLocations() {\n    48→    List<Location> allLocations = locationRepository.findAll();\n    49→    return locationDtoAssembler.toDtoList(allLocations);\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  @Override\n    53→  public String bookNewCargo(String origin, String destination, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    54→    TrackingId trackingId =\n    55→        bookingService.bookNewCargo(\n    56→            new UnLocode(origin), new UnLocode(destination), arrivalDeadline);\n    57→    return trackingId.getIdString();\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  @Override\n    61→  public CargoRoute loadCargoForRouting(String trackingId) {\n    62→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(new TrackingId(trackingId));\n    63→    return cargoRouteDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo);\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public void assignCargoToRoute(String trackingIdStr, RouteCandidate routeCandidateDTO) {\n    68→    Itinerary itinerary =\n    69→        itineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.fromDTO(\n    70→            routeCandidateDTO, voyageRepository, locationRepository);\n    71→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(trackingIdStr);\n    72→\n    73→    bookingService.assignCargoToRoute(itinerary, trackingId);\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  @Override\n    77→  public void changeDestination(String trackingId, String destinationUnLocode) {\n    78→    bookingService.changeDestination(new TrackingId(trackingId), new UnLocode(destinationUnLocode));\n    79→  }\n    80→\n    81→  @Override\n    82→  public void changeDeadline(String trackingId, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    83→    bookingService.changeDeadline(new TrackingId(trackingId), arrivalDeadline);\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  @Override\n    87→  // TODO [DDD] Is this the correct DTO here?\n    88→  public List<CargoRoute> listAllCargos() {\n    89→    List<Cargo> cargos = cargoRepository.findAll();\n    90→    List<CargoRoute> routes;\n    91→\n    92→    routes = cargos.stream().map(cargoRouteDtoAssembler::toDto).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    93→\n    94→    return routes;\n    95→  }\n    96→\n    97→  @Override\n    98→  public List<String> listAllTrackingIds() {\n    99→    List<String> trackingIds = new ArrayList<>();\n   100→    cargoRepository\n   101→        .findAll()\n   102→        .forEach(cargo -> trackingIds.add(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n   103→\n   104→    return trackingIds;\n   105→  }\n   106→\n   107→  @Override\n   108→  public CargoStatus loadCargoForTracking(String trackingIdValue) {\n   109→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(trackingIdValue);\n   110→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n   111→\n   112→    if (cargo == null) {\n   113→      return null;\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→    List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents =\n   117→        handlingEventRepository\n   118→            .lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId)\n   119→            .getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n   120→\n   121→    return cargoStatusDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo, handlingEvents);\n   122→  }\n   123→\n   124→  @Override\n   125→  public List<RouteCandidate> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(String trackingId) {\n   126→    List<Itinerary> itineraries =\n   127→        bookingService.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(new TrackingId(trackingId));\n   128→\n   129→    List<RouteCandidate> routeCandidates =\n   130→        itineraries\n   131→            .stream()\n   132→            .map(itineraryCandidateDtoAssembler::toDto)\n   133→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n   134→\n   135→    return routeCandidates;\n   136→  }\n   137→}\n   138→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"0f7e2681-6195-4007-88c5-5dc79bac10d7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B9fcJM3coDw1nCrx5yqNcG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     8→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles listing cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    15→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    16→ * interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    19→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    20→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    21→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ */\n    23→@Named\n    24→@RequestScoped\n    25→public class ListCargo {\n    26→\n    27→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    28→\n    29→  private List<CargoRoute> notRoutedCargos;\n    30→  private List<CargoRoute> routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    31→  private List<CargoRoute> claimedCargos;\n    32→\n    33→  @PostConstruct\n    34→  public void init() {\n    35→    List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    36→    notRoutedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(route -> !route.isRouted()).collect(toList());\n    37→    routedUnclaimedCargos =\n    38→        cargos.stream().filter(route -> route.isRouted() && !route.isClaimed()).collect(toList());\n    39→    claimedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(CargoRoute::isClaimed).collect(toList());\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public List<CargoRoute> getNotRoutedCargos() {\n    43→    return notRoutedCargos;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public List<CargoRoute> getRoutedUnclaimedCargos() {\n    47→    return routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public List<CargoRoute> getClaimedCargos() {\n    51→    return claimedCargos;\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"eb67a455-ebed-4f00-9cf9-0ed8752a3b33"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WyqZV6psCBa8SeCn6eTCSP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→import javax.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    10→import javax.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    11→import javax.faces.flow.FlowScoped;\n    12→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    13→import javax.inject.Named;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    16→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * Handles booking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    20→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    21→ * interface.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    24→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    25→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    26→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    27→ */\n    28→@Named\n    29→@FlowScoped(\"booking\")\n    30→public class Booking implements Serializable {\n    31→\n    32→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    33→\n    34→  private static final long MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION = 1; // Journey should be 1 day minimum.\n    35→\n    36→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    37→  @Inject private FacesContext context;\n    38→\n    39→  private LocalDate today = null;\n    40→  private List<Location> locations;\n    41→\n    42→  private String originUnlocode;\n    43→  private String originName;\n    44→  private String destinationName;\n    45→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    46→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    47→\n    48→  private boolean bookable = false;\n    49→  private long duration = -1;\n    50→\n    51→  @PostConstruct\n    52→  public void init() {\n    53→    today = LocalDate.now();\n    54→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    58→    List<Location> filteredLocations = new ArrayList<>();\n    59→    String locationToRemove = null;\n    60→\n    61→    if (context.getViewRoot().getViewId().endsWith(\"destination.xhtml\")) {\n    62→      // In the destination menu, origin can't be selected.\n    63→      locationToRemove = originUnlocode;\n    64→    } else { // Vice-versa.\n    65→      if (destinationUnlocode != null) {\n    66→        locationToRemove = destinationUnlocode;\n    67→      }\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    for (Location location : locations) {\n    71→      if (!location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(locationToRemove)) {\n    72→        filteredLocations.add(location);\n    73→      }\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    return filteredLocations;\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→  public String getOriginUnlocode() {\n    80→    return originUnlocode;\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  public void setOriginUnlocode(String originUnlocode) {\n    84→    this.originUnlocode = originUnlocode;\n    85→    this.originName =\n    86→        locations\n    87→            .stream()\n    88→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(originUnlocode))\n    89→            .findAny()\n    90→            .get()\n    91→            .getName();\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  public String getOriginName() {\n    95→    return originName;\n    96→  }\n    97→\n    98→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n    99→    return destinationUnlocode;\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n   103→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n   104→    this.destinationName =\n   105→        locations\n   106→            .stream()\n   107→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(destinationUnlocode))\n   108→            .findAny()\n   109→            .get()\n   110→            .getName();\n   111→  }\n   112→\n   113→  public String getDestinationName() {\n   114→    return destinationName;\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  public LocalDate getToday() {\n   118→    return today;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n   122→    return arrivalDeadline;\n   123→  }\n   124→\n   125→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n   126→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  public long getDuration() {\n   130→    return duration;\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  public boolean isBookable() {\n   134→    return bookable;\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  public void deadlineUpdated() {\n   138→    duration = ChronoUnit.DAYS.between(today, arrivalDeadline);\n   139→\n   140→    if (duration >= MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION) {\n   141→      bookable = true;\n   142→    } else {\n   143→      bookable = false;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:durationPanel\");\n   147→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:bookBtn\");\n   148→  }\n   149→\n   150→  public String register() {\n   151→    if (!originUnlocode.equals(destinationUnlocode)) {\n   152→      bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline);\n   153→    } else {\n   154→      // UI now prevents from selecting same origin/destination\n   155→      FacesMessage message = new FacesMessage(\"Origin and destination cannot be the same.\");\n   156→      message.setSeverity(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR);\n   157→      context.addMessage(null, message);\n   158→      return null;\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   162→  }\n   163→\n   164→  public String getReturnValue() {\n   165→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   166→  }\n   167→}\n   168→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"338e70bc-d73c-45be-a4b4-7f9ff9d9dbac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GG4s3r1yofZJF9aS6QHW1E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     6→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import javax.inject.Named;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles tracking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the public\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    18→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the public tracking controller. However,\n    19→ * there is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    20→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Named(\"admin.track\")\n    23→@ViewScoped\n    24→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    29→\n    30→  private List<String> trackingIds;\n    31→  private String trackingId;\n    32→  private CargoStatus cargo;\n    33→\n    34→  public List<String> getTrackingIds(String query) {\n    35→    return trackingIds;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    39→    return trackingId;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    43→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public CargoStatus getCargo() {\n    47→    return this.cargo;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  @PostConstruct\n    51→  public void init() {\n    52→    trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public void onTrackById() {\n    56→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(this.trackingId);\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016wkb5VmNEvRKSXMLbN9Lem","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"e25ea47c-2d5b-41cc-8043-2b021578f60f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ko9cBsMaNpe6bvFKEE5hMH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     4→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     5→import javax.inject.Named;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Handles viewing cargo details. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    11→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the\n    12→ * tracking user interface.\n    13→ *\n    14→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    15→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    16→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    17→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    18→ */\n    19→@Named\n    20→@RequestScoped\n    21→public class CargoDetails {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    24→\n    25→  private String trackingId;\n    26→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    27→\n    28→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    29→    return trackingId;\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    33→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    37→    return cargo;\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public void load() {\n    41→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what