{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DXeZsy8T7H8sYKMVpiw554","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Xvd6Xcjg1vcD5Nv9zKGTkS","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor application layer Java files","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the application layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- javax.* imports → jakarta.* imports (Quarkus 3.x uses Jakarta EE 10 namespace)\n- @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped + @Transactional\n- @Singleton @Startup → @ApplicationScoped with @Startup (io.quarkus.runtime.Startup)\n- @TransactionAttribute → @Transactional\n- @PersistenceContext → @Inject (Quarkus manages EntityManager injection via CDI)\n- javax.ejb.* → remove EJB imports, use CDI equivalents\n- javax.persistence.* → jakarta.persistence.*\n- javax.inject.* → jakarta.inject.*\n- javax.enterprise.* → jakarta.enterprise.*\n- javax.annotation.* → jakarta.annotation.*\n- javax.validation.* → jakarta.validation.*\n- java.util.logging.Logger stays the same but we remove the custom LoggerProducer and use @Inject directly\n\nFiles to refactor (READ each file first, then WRITE the updated version):\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/BookingService.java - Update javax.validation → jakarta.validation\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/HandlingEventService.java - Update imports\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/CargoInspectionService.java - No changes likely needed (it's an interface)\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/ApplicationEvents.java - No changes likely needed\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultBookingService.java - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n6. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultCargoInspectionService.java - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n7. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultHandlingEventService.java - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n8. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java - javax.persistence → jakarta.persistence\n9. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/DateConverter.java - No changes needed\n10. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/RestConfiguration.java - Replace with simple Quarkus JAX-RS Application class using jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath and jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application, remove Jersey dependency\n11. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/SampleDataGenerator.java - Replace @Singleton @Startup with @ApplicationScoped and use io.quarkus.runtime.Startup annotation, replace @TransactionAttribute with @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n\nFor RestConfiguration.java, the new content should be:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n\n@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\npublic class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n}\n```\n\nFor SampleDataGenerator.java, replace:\n- import javax.annotation.PostConstruct → import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct\n- import javax.ejb.Singleton → remove\n- import javax.ejb.Startup → import io.quarkus.runtime.Startup\n- import javax.ejb.TransactionAttribute; import javax.ejb.TransactionAttributeType → import jakarta.transaction.Transactional\n- import javax.inject.Inject → import jakarta.inject.Inject\n- import javax.persistence.EntityManager → import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager\n- import javax.persistence.LockModeType → import jakarta.persistence.LockModeType\n- import javax.persistence.NoResultException → import jakarta.persistence.NoResultException\n- import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext → remove (use @Inject instead)\n- @Singleton @Startup → @ApplicationScoped @Startup\n- @PersistenceContext → @Inject\n- @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED) → @Transactional\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file, make changes, and write the updated version. Do this for ALL 11 files listed above.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":241,"cache_read_input_tokens":88225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":241,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":12032},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"10230027-3b4e-40e0-9c60-2331e44aae21"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DXeZsy8T7H8sYKMVpiw554","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01F4hrVcLkPs9psAo2LgV4Z1","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor domain model Java files","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the domain model layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- ALL javax.* imports → jakarta.* equivalents\n- javax.persistence.* → jakarta.persistence.*\n- javax.inject.* → jakarta.inject.*\n- javax.enterprise.* → jakarta.enterprise.*\n- javax.validation.* → jakarta.validation.*\n\nFiles to refactor (READ each file first, then WRITE the updated version):\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Cargo.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Delivery.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/HandlingActivity.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Itinerary.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Leg.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n6. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/RouteSpecification.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n7. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/TrackingId.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n8. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/CargoRepository.java - check for javax imports\n9. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/RoutingStatus.java - likely no changes\n10. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/TransportStatus.java - likely no changes\n11. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEvent.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n12. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventFactory.java - javax→jakarta\n13. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingHistory.java - javax imports if any\n14. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventRepository.java - check for javax\n15. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/CannotCreateHandlingEventException.java - javax.ejb.ApplicationException → remove (just make it a regular exception)\n16. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/UnknownCargoException.java - check imports\n17. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/UnknownLocationException.java - check imports\n18. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/UnknownVoyageException.java - check imports\n19. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/Location.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n20. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/LocationRepository.java - check imports\n21. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/SampleLocations.java - likely no changes\n22. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/UnLocode.java - javax→jakarta\n23. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/Voyage.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n24. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/VoyageNumber.java - javax→jakarta\n25. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/VoyageRepository.java - check imports\n26. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/Schedule.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n27. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/CarrierMovement.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n28. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/SampleVoyages.java - likely no changes\n29. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/service/RoutingService.java - check imports\n30. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/shared/*.java - check all files for javax imports\n\nIMPORTANT: Read EVERY file listed above, make the javax→jakarta changes, and write the updated version. Only write files that actually need changes.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":241,"cache_read_input_tokens":88225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":241,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":12032},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"9e9faa79-0a8c-4e75-9698-af3c728b8416"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DXeZsy8T7H8sYKMVpiw554","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01LTomx7EQFFRmt3d5FcqNLv","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor infrastructure Java files","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the infrastructure layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKEY MIGRATION:\n\n## JMS → CDI Events\nThe JMS-based messaging must be replaced with CDI Events (synchronous in-process event bus). This is a major refactoring.\n\n### JmsApplicationEvents.java → CdiApplicationEvents.java\nReplace the JMS-based implementation with CDI events. Create a new file:\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CdiApplicationEvents.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class CdiApplicationEvents implements ApplicationEvents {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<CargoHandledEvent> cargoHandledEvent;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<CargoMisdirectedEvent> cargoMisdirectedEvent;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<CargoArrivedEvent> cargoArrivedEvent;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt> handlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent;\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event) {\n        Cargo cargo = event.getCargo();\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was handled {0}\", cargo);\n        cargoHandledEvent.fire(new CargoHandledEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was misdirected {0}\", cargo);\n        cargoMisdirectedEvent.fire(new CargoMisdirectedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo has arrived {0}\", cargo);\n        cargoArrivedEvent.fire(new CargoArrivedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Received handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        handlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent.fire(attempt);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCreate event classes in `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/`:\n\n**CargoHandledEvent.java:**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\npublic class CargoHandledEvent {\n    private final String trackingId;\n    \n    public CargoHandledEvent(String trackingId) {\n        this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    }\n    \n    public String getTrackingId() {\n        return trackingId;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoMisdirectedEvent.java:**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\npublic class CargoMisdirectedEvent {\n    private final String trackingId;\n    \n    public CargoMisdirectedEvent(String trackingId) {\n        this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    }\n    \n    public String getTrackingId() {\n        return trackingId;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoArrivedEvent.java:**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\npublic class CargoArrivedEvent {\n    private final String trackingId;\n    \n    public CargoArrivedEvent(String trackingId) {\n        this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    }\n    \n    public String getTrackingId() {\n        return trackingId;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Replace JMS Consumers with CDI Event Observers\n\nCreate `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CargoEventObservers.java`:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class CargoEventObservers {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    CargoInspectionService cargoInspectionService;\n\n    @Inject\n    HandlingEventService handlingEventService;\n\n    public void onCargoHandled(@Observes CargoHandledEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing cargo handled event for tracking ID: {0}\", event.getTrackingId());\n        cargoInspectionService.inspectCargo(new TrackingId(event.getTrackingId()));\n    }\n\n    public void onCargoMisdirected(@Observes CargoMisdirectedEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} misdirected.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n\n    public void onCargoArrived(@Observes CargoArrivedEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} delivered.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n\n    public void onHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(@Observes HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        try {\n            handlingEventService.registerHandlingEvent(\n                attempt.getCompletionTime(),\n                attempt.getTrackingId(),\n                attempt.getVoyageNumber(),\n                attempt.getUnLocode(),\n                attempt.getType());\n        } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n            logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Rejected handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Delete old JMS files\nDelete (or overwrite with empty marker) these files since they're no longer needed:\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/JmsApplicationEvents.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/CargoHandledConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/DeliveredCargoConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java\n\nTo \"delete\" them, just overwrite each with a comment explaining it was removed during migration, or better yet, write them as empty package-info.java files. Actually, since deleting is complex, just OVERWRITE each old JMS file to be an empty class with no imports that would fail (or a package-info). The cleanest approach: overwrite each with minimal valid Java that compiles but does nothing.\n\nActually the simplest approach is to DELETE the entire jms directory contents by overwriting each file to have a valid but empty/no-op class body. Let me suggest a different approach: since we can't delete files easily, let's just replace each JMS consumer/producer with a stub that has no JMS imports.\n\nFor each old JMS file, OVERWRITE it with a stub class that has a package statement but no code (just enough to compile):\n\nFor example, replace JmsApplicationEvents.java with:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n// This class has been replaced by CdiApplicationEvents during Quarkus migration.\n// Kept as empty stub to avoid build issues with file-based removal.\n```\n\nActually, the cleanest approach: Since Quarkus uses CDI and won't scan classes that don't have annotations, simply remove all the javax.jms and javax.ejb imports and make the classes empty stubs. But even simpler - just replace them with package-info or empty class.\n\nDO THE FOLLOWING:\n1. Create the 4 new files described above (CdiApplicationEvents, CargoHandledEvent, CargoMisdirectedEvent, CargoArrivedEvent, CargoEventObservers)\n2. Delete old JMS files by overwriting them with: just the package statement (no class declaration) - actually that won't compile. Best to just keep them with package statement and an empty class/interface with no problematic imports.\n\nFor each old JMS file, write this pattern:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n// Removed during Quarkus migration - replaced by CDI events\n```\nWait, that's not valid Java. Let me use:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n/**\n * Removed during Quarkus migration - replaced by CDI events in\n * org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging package.\n */\nclass [OriginalClassName]Removed {}\n```\n\n### Other infrastructure files to refactor:\n\n**LoggerProducer.java** - Update javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.InjectionPoint;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class LoggerProducer {\n\n    @Produces\n    public Logger produceLogger(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n        String loggerName = extractLoggerName(injectionPoint);\n        return Logger.getLogger(loggerName);\n    }\n\n    private String extractLoggerName(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n        if (injectionPoint.getBean() == null) {\n            return injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass().getName();\n        }\n        if (injectionPoint.getBean().getName() == null) {\n            return injectionPoint.getBean().getBeanClass().getName();\n        }\n        return injectionPoint.getBean().getName();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoUpdated.java** - Update javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi;\n\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n\n@Qualifier\n@Retention(RUNTIME)\n@Target({FIELD, PARAMETER})\npublic @interface CargoUpdated {}\n```\n\n**JPA Repository files** - Update javax→jakarta:\n\n**JpaCargoRepository.java:**\n- javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped → jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped\n- javax.enterprise.event.Event → jakarta.enterprise.event.Event\n- javax.inject.Inject → jakarta.inject.Inject\n- javax.persistence.* → jakarta.persistence.*\n- @PersistenceContext → @Inject\n\n**JpaHandlingEventRepository.java** - same javax→jakarta pattern, @PersistenceContext → @Inject\n**JpaLocationRepository.java** - same\n**JpaVoyageRepository.java** - same\n\n**ExternalRoutingService.java** - Major refactoring needed:\n- Remove @Stateless, add @ApplicationScoped\n- Remove @Resource for graphTraversalUrl, use @ConfigProperty from Quarkus\n- Replace JAX-RS Client with Quarkus REST Client or simple URL approach\n- javax→jakarta\n\nNew version:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.client.WebTarget;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.GenericType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitEdge;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitPath;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"graph.traversal.url\")\n    String graphTraversalUrl;\n\n    private WebTarget graphTraversalResource;\n\n    @Inject\n    LocationRepository locationRepository;\n\n    @Inject\n    VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    public void init() {\n        graphTraversalResource = ClientBuilder.newClient().target(graphTraversalUrl);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n        String origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n        String destination = routeSpecification.getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n\n        List<TransitPath> transitPaths =\n            graphTraversalResource\n                .queryParam(\"origin\", origin)\n                .queryParam(\"destination\", destination)\n                .request(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n                .get(new GenericType<List<TransitPath>>() {});\n\n        List<Itinerary> itineraries = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        transitPaths.stream()\n            .map(this::toItinerary)\n            .forEach(itinerary -> {\n                if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n                    itineraries.add(itinerary);\n                } else {\n                    logger.log(Level.FINE, \"Received itinerary that did not satisfy the route specification\");\n                }\n            });\n\n        return itineraries;\n    }\n\n    private Itinerary toItinerary(TransitPath transitPath) {\n        List<Leg> legs = transitPath.getTransitEdges().stream().map(this::toLeg).collect(Collectors.toList());\n        return new Itinerary(legs);\n    }\n\n    private Leg toLeg(TransitEdge edge) {\n        return new Leg(\n            voyageRepository.find(new VoyageNumber(edge.getVoyageNumber())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getFromUnLocode())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getToUnLocode())),\n            edge.getFromDate(),\n            edge.getToDate());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file first, then write the updated version. Create ALL the new CDI event files. Update ALL the old JMS files. Update ALL infrastructure files listed above.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":241,"cache_read_input_tokens":88225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":241,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":12032},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"dd067266-9974-4b95-a149-8646df0acd9e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DXeZsy8T7H8sYKMVpiw554","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017mMqNkQ2CqnaoxpBvKzHTj","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor interfaces layer Java files","prompt":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the interfaces layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- ALL javax.* → jakarta.* (javax.inject→jakarta.inject, javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, etc.)\n- @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional\n- @Singleton → @ApplicationScoped\n- JSF classes (@Named, @ViewScoped, @RequestScoped with JSF) → remove JSF UI, keep as stub or remove\n- @MessageDriven → Remove (replaced by CDI events)\n- javax.faces.* → Remove entirely (Quarkus doesn't support JSF)\n- javax.batch.* → Replace with Quarkus scheduler\n- @Schedule → @Scheduled (io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled)\n- javax.xml.bind → jakarta.xml.bind\n\nFILES TO REFACTOR:\n\n### REST Endpoints (keep and update):\n\n**HandlingReportService.java** - Replace @Stateless with @ApplicationScoped, javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Transactional\n@Path(\"/handling\")\npublic class HandlingReportService {\n\n    @Inject\n    ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n\n    @POST\n    @Path(\"/reports\")\n    @Consumes({\"application/json\", \"application/xml\"})\n    public void submitReport(\n            @NotNull(message = \"Missing handling report.\") @Valid HandlingReport handlingReport) {\n        LocalDateTime completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(handlingReport.getCompletionTime());\n        VoyageNumber voyageNumber = null;\n\n        if (handlingReport.getVoyageNumber() != null) {\n            voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(handlingReport.getVoyageNumber());\n        }\n\n        HandlingEvent.Type type = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(handlingReport.getEventType());\n        UnLocode unLocode = new UnLocode(handlingReport.getUnLocode());\n        TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(handlingReport.getTrackingId());\n\n        HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n                new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n                        LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, type, unLocode);\n\n        applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**HandlingReport.java** - javax.validation→jakarta.validation, javax.xml.bind→jakarta.xml.bind:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\nimport jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n\n@XmlRootElement\npublic class HandlingReport {\n    // ... keep all fields and methods, just update imports\n}\n```\n\n**HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java** - No javax imports, just check\n\n### Pathfinder API (keep and update):\n\n**GraphTraversalService.java** - @Stateless→@ApplicationScoped, javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Random;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Pattern;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal.GraphDao;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/graph-traversal\")\npublic class GraphTraversalService {\n    // ... keep all methods, just update imports and annotation\n}\n```\n\n**TransitPath.java** - javax.xml.bind→jakarta.xml.bind\n**TransitEdge.java** - check imports\n**GraphDao.java** - javax.enterprise→jakarta.enterprise\n\n### SSE endpoint:\n\n**RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java** - Major refactoring: @Singleton→@ApplicationScoped, javax→jakarta, update SSE:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.OutboundSseEvent;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.Sse;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.SseBroadcaster;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.SseEventSink;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/cargo\")\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n    // ... keep all the logic, just update imports and annotations\n}\n```\n\n**RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java** - No javax imports likely\n**LocationViewAdapter.java** - No javax imports\n\n### Booking facade (keep for internal use by REST):\n\n**BookingServiceFacade.java** - check imports\n**DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java** - javax→jakarta\n\n### Assemblers - check and update:\n- CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java\n- CargoStatusDtoAssembler.java \n- ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.java\n- LocationDtoAssembler.java\n- TrackingEventsDtoAssembler.java\n\n### DTOs:\n- CargoRoute.java, CargoStatus.java, Location.java, Leg.java, RouteCandidate.java, TrackingEvents.java\n\n### JSF Web Beans - Replace with REST endpoints or stubs:\nSince JSF is not supported in Quarkus, we need to REPLACE the JSF backing beans with REST controllers.\n\nCreate a new REST controller that exposes the booking functionality:\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/rest/BookingRestService.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.rest;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.*;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.*;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/booking\")\n@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\npublic class BookingRestService {\n\n    @Inject\n    BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/cargos\")\n    public List<CargoRoute> listAllCargos() {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/locations\")\n    public List<Location> listLocations() {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/cargos/{trackingId}\")\n    public CargoRoute getCargo(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId) {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/tracking/{trackingId}\")\n    public CargoStatus trackCargo(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId) {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @POST\n    @Path(\"/cargos\")\n    @Transactional\n    public Response bookCargo(BookCargoRequest request) {\n        String trackingId = bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(\n            request.getOrigin(),\n            request.getDestination(),\n            request.getArrivalDeadline());\n        return Response.ok(new BookCargoResponse(trackingId)).build();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/cargos/{trackingId}/routes\")\n    public List<RouteCandidate> requestRoutes(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId) {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @PUT\n    @Path(\"/cargos/{trackingId}/route\")\n    @Transactional\n    public Response assignRoute(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId, RouteCandidate route) {\n        bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n        return Response.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/trackingids\")\n    public List<String> listTrackingIds() {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCreate request/response DTOs:\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/rest/BookCargoRequest.java`\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.rest;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\n\npublic class BookCargoRequest {\n    private String origin;\n    private String destination;\n    private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n\n    public BookCargoRequest() {}\n\n    public String getOrigin() { return origin; }\n    public void setOrigin(String origin) { this.origin = origin; }\n    public String getDestination() { return destination; }\n    public void setDestination(String destination) { this.destination = destination; }\n    public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() { return arrivalDeadline; }\n    public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) { this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline; }\n}\n```\n\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/rest/BookCargoResponse.java`\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.rest;\n\npublic class BookCargoResponse {\n    private String trackingId;\n\n    public BookCargoResponse() {}\n    public BookCargoResponse(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n    public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n}\n```\n\n### File batch processing → Quarkus Scheduler:\n\n**UploadDirectoryScanner.java** - Replace @Stateless @Schedule with Quarkus @Scheduled:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    EventFileProcessor eventFileProcessor;\n\n    @Scheduled(every = \"120s\")\n    public void processFiles() {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Scanning for event files...\");\n        eventFileProcessor.processEventFiles();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCreate a new `EventFileProcessor.java` that replaces the batch job:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.io.BufferedReader;\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.FileReader;\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.time.format.DateTimeParseException;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class EventFileProcessor {\n\n    private static final String UPLOAD_DIRECTORY = \"/tmp/cargo-tracker/upload\";\n    private static final String ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY = \"/tmp/cargo-tracker/archive\";\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public void processEventFiles() {\n        File uploadDir = new File(UPLOAD_DIRECTORY);\n        if (!uploadDir.exists()) {\n            uploadDir.mkdirs();\n            return;\n        }\n\n        File[] files = uploadDir.listFiles();\n        if (files == null || files.length == 0) {\n            return;\n        }\n\n        File archiveDir = new File(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY);\n        if (!archiveDir.exists()) {\n            archiveDir.mkdirs();\n        }\n\n        for (File file : files) {\n            processFile(file, archiveDir);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void processFile(File file, File archiveDir) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing event file: {0}\", file.getName());\n        try (BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(file))) {\n            String line;\n            while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {\n                try {\n                    processLine(line);\n                } catch (Exception e) {\n                    logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Error processing line: \" + line, e);\n                }\n            }\n            // Move to archive\n            file.renameTo(new File(archiveDir, file.getName()));\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error processing file: \" + file.getName(), e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void processLine(String line) {\n        String[] parts = line.split(\",\");\n        if (parts.length != 5) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Wrong number of data elements in line: \" + line);\n        }\n\n        LocalDateTime completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(parts[0]);\n        TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(parts[1]);\n        VoyageNumber voyageNumber = parts[2].isEmpty() ? null : new VoyageNumber(parts[2]);\n        UnLocode unLocode = new UnLocode(parts[3]);\n        HandlingEvent.Type eventType = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(parts[4]);\n\n        HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt = new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, eventType, unLocode);\n\n        applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### JSF Backing Beans - Convert to stubs (won't be used but need to compile):\nFor the JSF web beans that reference javax.faces, we need to either:\na) Delete them (but files can't be deleted)\nb) Convert them to simple POJOs without JSF dependencies\n\nFor each JSF bean file, REPLACE it with a minimal stub that just has the package declaration and a comment. Remove all JSF-specific code.\n\nFiles to stub out:\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ListCargo.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/Booking.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/Track.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/CargoDetails.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeDestination.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeDestinationDialog.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeArrivalDeadline.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ItinerarySelection.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/mobile/EventLogger.java\n\nFor each of these, write a minimal version like:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\n// Removed during Quarkus migration - JSF not supported\n// Functionality replaced by BookingRestService\npublic class ListCargo {\n}\n```\n\n### Also refactor batch files to stubs since Jakarta Batch is removed:\n- EventItemReader.java → stub\n- EventItemWriter.java → stub\n- EventFilesCheckpoint.java → keep as-is (plain POJO)\n- FileProcessorJobListener.java → stub\n- LineParseExceptionListener.java → stub\n- EventLineParseException.java → keep as-is (plain exception class)\n\nFor batch stubs, remove javax.batch imports:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n// Removed during Quarkus migration - replaced by EventFileProcessor\npublic class EventItemReader {\n}\n```\n\n### Tracking web (public):\nCheck if there are tracking web files:\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/tracking/web/Track.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/tracking/web/CargoTrackingViewAdapter.java\n\nIf they exist and use JSF, stub them out too.\n\nIMPORTANT: READ each file first, then WRITE the updated version. Do ALL files listed above. Create ALL new files (BookingRestService, BookCargoRequest, BookCargoResponse, EventFileProcessor).","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":241,"cache_read_input_tokens":88225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":241,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":12032},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"0f8373ae-5f46-4610-b49b-46894ddc2e23"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the application layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- javax.* imports → jakarta.* imports (Quarkus 3.x uses Jakarta EE 10 namespace)\n- @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped + @Transactional\n- @Singleton @Startup → @ApplicationScoped with @Startup (io.quarkus.runtime.Startup)\n- @TransactionAttribute → @Transactional\n- @PersistenceContext → @Inject (Quarkus manages EntityManager injection via CDI)\n- javax.ejb.* → remove EJB imports, use CDI equivalents\n- javax.persistence.* → jakarta.persistence.*\n- javax.inject.* → jakarta.inject.*\n- javax.enterprise.* → jakarta.enterprise.*\n- javax.annotation.* → jakarta.annotation.*\n- javax.validation.* → jakarta.validation.*\n- java.util.logging.Logger stays the same but we remove the custom LoggerProducer and use @Inject directly\n\nFiles to refactor (READ each file first, then WRITE the updated version):\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/BookingService.java - Update javax.validation → jakarta.validation\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/HandlingEventService.java - Update imports\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/CargoInspectionService.java - No changes likely needed (it's an interface)\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/ApplicationEvents.java - No changes likely needed\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultBookingService.java - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n6. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultCargoInspectionService.java - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n7. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultHandlingEventService.java - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n8. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java - javax.persistence → jakarta.persistence\n9. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/DateConverter.java - No changes needed\n10. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/RestConfiguration.java - Replace with simple Quarkus JAX-RS Application class using jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath and jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application, remove Jersey dependency\n11. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/SampleDataGenerator.java - Replace @Singleton @Startup with @ApplicationScoped and use io.quarkus.runtime.Startup annotation, replace @TransactionAttribute with @Transactional, javax→jakarta\n\nFor RestConfiguration.java, the new content should be:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n\n@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\npublic class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n}\n```\n\nFor SampleDataGenerator.java, replace:\n- import javax.annotation.PostConstruct → import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct\n- import javax.ejb.Singleton → remove\n- import javax.ejb.Startup → import io.quarkus.runtime.Startup\n- import javax.ejb.TransactionAttribute; import javax.ejb.TransactionAttributeType → import jakarta.transaction.Transactional\n- import javax.inject.Inject → import jakarta.inject.Inject\n- import javax.persistence.EntityManager → import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager\n- import javax.persistence.LockModeType → import jakarta.persistence.LockModeType\n- import javax.persistence.NoResultException → import jakarta.persistence.NoResultException\n- import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext → remove (use @Inject instead)\n- @Singleton @Startup → @ApplicationScoped @Startup\n- @PersistenceContext → @Inject\n- @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED) → @Transactional\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file, make changes, and write the updated version. Do this for ALL 11 files listed above."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Xvd6Xcjg1vcD5Nv9zKGTkS","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"1040b9e4-7a3e-43b9-a696-bfc717e6990e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the domain model layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- ALL javax.* imports → jakarta.* equivalents\n- javax.persistence.* → jakarta.persistence.*\n- javax.inject.* → jakarta.inject.*\n- javax.enterprise.* → jakarta.enterprise.*\n- javax.validation.* → jakarta.validation.*\n\nFiles to refactor (READ each file first, then WRITE the updated version):\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Cargo.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Delivery.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/HandlingActivity.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Itinerary.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Leg.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n6. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/RouteSpecification.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n7. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/TrackingId.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n8. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/CargoRepository.java - check for javax imports\n9. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/RoutingStatus.java - likely no changes\n10. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/TransportStatus.java - likely no changes\n11. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEvent.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n12. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventFactory.java - javax→jakarta\n13. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingHistory.java - javax imports if any\n14. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventRepository.java - check for javax\n15. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/CannotCreateHandlingEventException.java - javax.ejb.ApplicationException → remove (just make it a regular exception)\n16. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/UnknownCargoException.java - check imports\n17. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/UnknownLocationException.java - check imports\n18. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/UnknownVoyageException.java - check imports\n19. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/Location.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n20. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/LocationRepository.java - check imports\n21. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/SampleLocations.java - likely no changes\n22. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/UnLocode.java - javax→jakarta\n23. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/Voyage.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n24. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/VoyageNumber.java - javax→jakarta\n25. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/VoyageRepository.java - check imports\n26. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/Schedule.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n27. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/CarrierMovement.java - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence\n28. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/SampleVoyages.java - likely no changes\n29. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/service/RoutingService.java - check imports\n30. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/shared/*.java - check all files for javax imports\n\nIMPORTANT: Read EVERY file listed above, make the javax→jakarta changes, and write the updated version. Only write files that actually need changes."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F4hrVcLkPs9psAo2LgV4Z1","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"649ec8b8-1863-4370-a8dc-d86fc9952b35"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the infrastructure layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKEY MIGRATION:\n\n## JMS → CDI Events\nThe JMS-based messaging must be replaced with CDI Events (synchronous in-process event bus). This is a major refactoring.\n\n### JmsApplicationEvents.java → CdiApplicationEvents.java\nReplace the JMS-based implementation with CDI events. Create a new file:\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CdiApplicationEvents.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class CdiApplicationEvents implements ApplicationEvents {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<CargoHandledEvent> cargoHandledEvent;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<CargoMisdirectedEvent> cargoMisdirectedEvent;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<CargoArrivedEvent> cargoArrivedEvent;\n\n    @Inject\n    Event<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt> handlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent;\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event) {\n        Cargo cargo = event.getCargo();\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was handled {0}\", cargo);\n        cargoHandledEvent.fire(new CargoHandledEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was misdirected {0}\", cargo);\n        cargoMisdirectedEvent.fire(new CargoMisdirectedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo has arrived {0}\", cargo);\n        cargoArrivedEvent.fire(new CargoArrivedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Received handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        handlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent.fire(attempt);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCreate event classes in `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/`:\n\n**CargoHandledEvent.java:**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\npublic class CargoHandledEvent {\n    private final String trackingId;\n    \n    public CargoHandledEvent(String trackingId) {\n        this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    }\n    \n    public String getTrackingId() {\n        return trackingId;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoMisdirectedEvent.java:**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\npublic class CargoMisdirectedEvent {\n    private final String trackingId;\n    \n    public CargoMisdirectedEvent(String trackingId) {\n        this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    }\n    \n    public String getTrackingId() {\n        return trackingId;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoArrivedEvent.java:**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\npublic class CargoArrivedEvent {\n    private final String trackingId;\n    \n    public CargoArrivedEvent(String trackingId) {\n        this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    }\n    \n    public String getTrackingId() {\n        return trackingId;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Replace JMS Consumers with CDI Event Observers\n\nCreate `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CargoEventObservers.java`:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class CargoEventObservers {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    CargoInspectionService cargoInspectionService;\n\n    @Inject\n    HandlingEventService handlingEventService;\n\n    public void onCargoHandled(@Observes CargoHandledEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing cargo handled event for tracking ID: {0}\", event.getTrackingId());\n        cargoInspectionService.inspectCargo(new TrackingId(event.getTrackingId()));\n    }\n\n    public void onCargoMisdirected(@Observes CargoMisdirectedEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} misdirected.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n\n    public void onCargoArrived(@Observes CargoArrivedEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} delivered.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n\n    public void onHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(@Observes HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        try {\n            handlingEventService.registerHandlingEvent(\n                attempt.getCompletionTime(),\n                attempt.getTrackingId(),\n                attempt.getVoyageNumber(),\n                attempt.getUnLocode(),\n                attempt.getType());\n        } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n            logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Rejected handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Delete old JMS files\nDelete (or overwrite with empty marker) these files since they're no longer needed:\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/JmsApplicationEvents.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/CargoHandledConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/DeliveredCargoConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java\n\nTo \"delete\" them, just overwrite each with a comment explaining it was removed during migration, or better yet, write them as empty package-info.java files. Actually, since deleting is complex, just OVERWRITE each old JMS file to be an empty class with no imports that would fail (or a package-info). The cleanest approach: overwrite each with minimal valid Java that compiles but does nothing.\n\nActually the simplest approach is to DELETE the entire jms directory contents by overwriting each file to have a valid but empty/no-op class body. Let me suggest a different approach: since we can't delete files easily, let's just replace each JMS consumer/producer with a stub that has no JMS imports.\n\nFor each old JMS file, OVERWRITE it with a stub class that has a package statement but no code (just enough to compile):\n\nFor example, replace JmsApplicationEvents.java with:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n// This class has been replaced by CdiApplicationEvents during Quarkus migration.\n// Kept as empty stub to avoid build issues with file-based removal.\n```\n\nActually, the cleanest approach: Since Quarkus uses CDI and won't scan classes that don't have annotations, simply remove all the javax.jms and javax.ejb imports and make the classes empty stubs. But even simpler - just replace them with package-info or empty class.\n\nDO THE FOLLOWING:\n1. Create the 4 new files described above (CdiApplicationEvents, CargoHandledEvent, CargoMisdirectedEvent, CargoArrivedEvent, CargoEventObservers)\n2. Delete old JMS files by overwriting them with: just the package statement (no class declaration) - actually that won't compile. Best to just keep them with package statement and an empty class/interface with no problematic imports.\n\nFor each old JMS file, write this pattern:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n// Removed during Quarkus migration - replaced by CDI events\n```\nWait, that's not valid Java. Let me use:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n/**\n * Removed during Quarkus migration - replaced by CDI events in\n * org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging package.\n */\nclass [OriginalClassName]Removed {}\n```\n\n### Other infrastructure files to refactor:\n\n**LoggerProducer.java** - Update javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.InjectionPoint;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class LoggerProducer {\n\n    @Produces\n    public Logger produceLogger(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n        String loggerName = extractLoggerName(injectionPoint);\n        return Logger.getLogger(loggerName);\n    }\n\n    private String extractLoggerName(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n        if (injectionPoint.getBean() == null) {\n            return injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass().getName();\n        }\n        if (injectionPoint.getBean().getName() == null) {\n            return injectionPoint.getBean().getBeanClass().getName();\n        }\n        return injectionPoint.getBean().getName();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoUpdated.java** - Update javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi;\n\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n\n@Qualifier\n@Retention(RUNTIME)\n@Target({FIELD, PARAMETER})\npublic @interface CargoUpdated {}\n```\n\n**JPA Repository files** - Update javax→jakarta:\n\n**JpaCargoRepository.java:**\n- javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped → jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped\n- javax.enterprise.event.Event → jakarta.enterprise.event.Event\n- javax.inject.Inject → jakarta.inject.Inject\n- javax.persistence.* → jakarta.persistence.*\n- @PersistenceContext → @Inject\n\n**JpaHandlingEventRepository.java** - same javax→jakarta pattern, @PersistenceContext → @Inject\n**JpaLocationRepository.java** - same\n**JpaVoyageRepository.java** - same\n\n**ExternalRoutingService.java** - Major refactoring needed:\n- Remove @Stateless, add @ApplicationScoped\n- Remove @Resource for graphTraversalUrl, use @ConfigProperty from Quarkus\n- Replace JAX-RS Client with Quarkus REST Client or simple URL approach\n- javax→jakarta\n\nNew version:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.client.WebTarget;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.GenericType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitEdge;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitPath;\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"graph.traversal.url\")\n    String graphTraversalUrl;\n\n    private WebTarget graphTraversalResource;\n\n    @Inject\n    LocationRepository locationRepository;\n\n    @Inject\n    VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    public void init() {\n        graphTraversalResource = ClientBuilder.newClient().target(graphTraversalUrl);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n        String origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n        String destination = routeSpecification.getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n\n        List<TransitPath> transitPaths =\n            graphTraversalResource\n                .queryParam(\"origin\", origin)\n                .queryParam(\"destination\", destination)\n                .request(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n                .get(new GenericType<List<TransitPath>>() {});\n\n        List<Itinerary> itineraries = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        transitPaths.stream()\n            .map(this::toItinerary)\n            .forEach(itinerary -> {\n                if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n                    itineraries.add(itinerary);\n                } else {\n                    logger.log(Level.FINE, \"Received itinerary that did not satisfy the route specification\");\n                }\n            });\n\n        return itineraries;\n    }\n\n    private Itinerary toItinerary(TransitPath transitPath) {\n        List<Leg> legs = transitPath.getTransitEdges().stream().map(this::toLeg).collect(Collectors.toList());\n        return new Itinerary(legs);\n    }\n\n    private Leg toLeg(TransitEdge edge) {\n        return new Leg(\n            voyageRepository.find(new VoyageNumber(edge.getVoyageNumber())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getFromUnLocode())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getToUnLocode())),\n            edge.getFromDate(),\n            edge.getToDate());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file first, then write the updated version. Create ALL the new CDI event files. Update ALL the old JMS files. Update ALL infrastructure files listed above."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LTomx7EQFFRmt3d5FcqNLv","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"3225b411-ee0b-4973-897c-4392a46e9171"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Quarkus. I need to refactor Java source files in the interfaces layer. The project is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- ALL javax.* → jakarta.* (javax.inject→jakarta.inject, javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, etc.)\n- @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional\n- @Singleton → @ApplicationScoped\n- JSF classes (@Named, @ViewScoped, @RequestScoped with JSF) → remove JSF UI, keep as stub or remove\n- @MessageDriven → Remove (replaced by CDI events)\n- javax.faces.* → Remove entirely (Quarkus doesn't support JSF)\n- javax.batch.* → Replace with Quarkus scheduler\n- @Schedule → @Scheduled (io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled)\n- javax.xml.bind → jakarta.xml.bind\n\nFILES TO REFACTOR:\n\n### REST Endpoints (keep and update):\n\n**HandlingReportService.java** - Replace @Stateless with @ApplicationScoped, javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Transactional\n@Path(\"/handling\")\npublic class HandlingReportService {\n\n    @Inject\n    ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n\n    @POST\n    @Path(\"/reports\")\n    @Consumes({\"application/json\", \"application/xml\"})\n    public void submitReport(\n            @NotNull(message = \"Missing handling report.\") @Valid HandlingReport handlingReport) {\n        LocalDateTime completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(handlingReport.getCompletionTime());\n        VoyageNumber voyageNumber = null;\n\n        if (handlingReport.getVoyageNumber() != null) {\n            voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(handlingReport.getVoyageNumber());\n        }\n\n        HandlingEvent.Type type = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(handlingReport.getEventType());\n        UnLocode unLocode = new UnLocode(handlingReport.getUnLocode());\n        TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(handlingReport.getTrackingId());\n\n        HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n                new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n                        LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, type, unLocode);\n\n        applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**HandlingReport.java** - javax.validation→jakarta.validation, javax.xml.bind→jakarta.xml.bind:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\nimport jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n\n@XmlRootElement\npublic class HandlingReport {\n    // ... keep all fields and methods, just update imports\n}\n```\n\n**HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java** - No javax imports, just check\n\n### Pathfinder API (keep and update):\n\n**GraphTraversalService.java** - @Stateless→@ApplicationScoped, javax→jakarta:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Random;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Pattern;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal.GraphDao;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/graph-traversal\")\npublic class GraphTraversalService {\n    // ... keep all methods, just update imports and annotation\n}\n```\n\n**TransitPath.java** - javax.xml.bind→jakarta.xml.bind\n**TransitEdge.java** - check imports\n**GraphDao.java** - javax.enterprise→jakarta.enterprise\n\n### SSE endpoint:\n\n**RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java** - Major refactoring: @Singleton→@ApplicationScoped, javax→jakarta, update SSE:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.OutboundSseEvent;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.Sse;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.SseBroadcaster;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.sse.SseEventSink;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/cargo\")\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n    // ... keep all the logic, just update imports and annotations\n}\n```\n\n**RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java** - No javax imports likely\n**LocationViewAdapter.java** - No javax imports\n\n### Booking facade (keep for internal use by REST):\n\n**BookingServiceFacade.java** - check imports\n**DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java** - javax→jakarta\n\n### Assemblers - check and update:\n- CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java\n- CargoStatusDtoAssembler.java \n- ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.java\n- LocationDtoAssembler.java\n- TrackingEventsDtoAssembler.java\n\n### DTOs:\n- CargoRoute.java, CargoStatus.java, Location.java, Leg.java, RouteCandidate.java, TrackingEvents.java\n\n### JSF Web Beans - Replace with REST endpoints or stubs:\nSince JSF is not supported in Quarkus, we need to REPLACE the JSF backing beans with REST controllers.\n\nCreate a new REST controller that exposes the booking functionality:\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/rest/BookingRestService.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.rest;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.*;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.*;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/booking\")\n@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\npublic class BookingRestService {\n\n    @Inject\n    BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/cargos\")\n    public List<CargoRoute> listAllCargos() {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/locations\")\n    public List<Location> listLocations() {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/cargos/{trackingId}\")\n    public CargoRoute getCargo(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId) {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/tracking/{trackingId}\")\n    public CargoStatus trackCargo(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId) {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @POST\n    @Path(\"/cargos\")\n    @Transactional\n    public Response bookCargo(BookCargoRequest request) {\n        String trackingId = bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(\n            request.getOrigin(),\n            request.getDestination(),\n            request.getArrivalDeadline());\n        return Response.ok(new BookCargoResponse(trackingId)).build();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/cargos/{trackingId}/routes\")\n    public List<RouteCandidate> requestRoutes(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId) {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @PUT\n    @Path(\"/cargos/{trackingId}/route\")\n    @Transactional\n    public Response assignRoute(@PathParam(\"trackingId\") String trackingId, RouteCandidate route) {\n        bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n        return Response.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/trackingids\")\n    public List<String> listTrackingIds() {\n        return bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCreate request/response DTOs:\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/rest/BookCargoRequest.java`\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.rest;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\n\npublic class BookCargoRequest {\n    private String origin;\n    private String destination;\n    private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n\n    public BookCargoRequest() {}\n\n    public String getOrigin() { return origin; }\n    public void setOrigin(String origin) { this.origin = origin; }\n    public String getDestination() { return destination; }\n    public void setDestination(String destination) { this.destination = destination; }\n    public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() { return arrivalDeadline; }\n    public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) { this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline; }\n}\n```\n\n`src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/rest/BookCargoResponse.java`\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.rest;\n\npublic class BookCargoResponse {\n    private String trackingId;\n\n    public BookCargoResponse() {}\n    public BookCargoResponse(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n    public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n}\n```\n\n### File batch processing → Quarkus Scheduler:\n\n**UploadDirectoryScanner.java** - Replace @Stateless @Schedule with Quarkus @Scheduled:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    EventFileProcessor eventFileProcessor;\n\n    @Scheduled(every = \"120s\")\n    public void processFiles() {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Scanning for event files...\");\n        eventFileProcessor.processEventFiles();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCreate a new `EventFileProcessor.java` that replaces the batch job:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.io.BufferedReader;\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.FileReader;\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.time.format.DateTimeParseException;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class EventFileProcessor {\n\n    private static final String UPLOAD_DIRECTORY = \"/tmp/cargo-tracker/upload\";\n    private static final String ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY = \"/tmp/cargo-tracker/archive\";\n\n    @Inject\n    Logger logger;\n\n    @Inject\n    ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n\n    @Transactional\n    public void processEventFiles() {\n        File uploadDir = new File(UPLOAD_DIRECTORY);\n        if (!uploadDir.exists()) {\n            uploadDir.mkdirs();\n            return;\n        }\n\n        File[] files = uploadDir.listFiles();\n        if (files == null || files.length == 0) {\n            return;\n        }\n\n        File archiveDir = new File(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY);\n        if (!archiveDir.exists()) {\n            archiveDir.mkdirs();\n        }\n\n        for (File file : files) {\n            processFile(file, archiveDir);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void processFile(File file, File archiveDir) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing event file: {0}\", file.getName());\n        try (BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(file))) {\n            String line;\n            while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {\n                try {\n                    processLine(line);\n                } catch (Exception e) {\n                    logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Error processing line: \" + line, e);\n                }\n            }\n            // Move to archive\n            file.renameTo(new File(archiveDir, file.getName()));\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error processing file: \" + file.getName(), e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void processLine(String line) {\n        String[] parts = line.split(\",\");\n        if (parts.length != 5) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Wrong number of data elements in line: \" + line);\n        }\n\n        LocalDateTime completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(parts[0]);\n        TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(parts[1]);\n        VoyageNumber voyageNumber = parts[2].isEmpty() ? null : new VoyageNumber(parts[2]);\n        UnLocode unLocode = new UnLocode(parts[3]);\n        HandlingEvent.Type eventType = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(parts[4]);\n\n        HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt = new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, eventType, unLocode);\n\n        applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### JSF Backing Beans - Convert to stubs (won't be used but need to compile):\nFor the JSF web beans that reference javax.faces, we need to either:\na) Delete them (but files can't be deleted)\nb) Convert them to simple POJOs without JSF dependencies\n\nFor each JSF bean file, REPLACE it with a minimal stub that just has the package declaration and a comment. Remove all JSF-specific code.\n\nFiles to stub out:\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ListCargo.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/Booking.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/Track.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/CargoDetails.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeDestination.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeDestinationDialog.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeArrivalDeadline.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ItinerarySelection.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/mobile/EventLogger.java\n\nFor each of these, write a minimal version like:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\n// Removed during Quarkus migration - JSF not supported\n// Functionality replaced by BookingRestService\npublic class ListCargo {\n}\n```\n\n### Also refactor batch files to stubs since Jakarta Batch is removed:\n- EventItemReader.java → stub\n- EventItemWriter.java → stub\n- EventFilesCheckpoint.java → keep as-is (plain POJO)\n- FileProcessorJobListener.java → stub\n- LineParseExceptionListener.java → stub\n- EventLineParseException.java → keep as-is (plain exception class)\n\nFor batch stubs, remove javax.batch imports:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n// Removed during Quarkus migration - replaced by EventFileProcessor\npublic class EventItemReader {\n}\n```\n\n### Tracking web (public):\nCheck if there are tracking web files:\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/tracking/web/Track.java\n- src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/tracking/web/CargoTrackingViewAdapter.java\n\nIf they exist and use JSF, stub them out too.\n\nIMPORTANT: READ each file first, then WRITE the updated version. Do ALL files listed above. Create ALL new files (BookingRestService, BookCargoRequest, BookCargoResponse, EventFileProcessor)."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017mMqNkQ2CqnaoxpBvKzHTj","session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"d3c8b12f-89a8-41cd-9379-1c19814d809e"}
