{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CsWbQkBcxPvMK5hkBW2Jsd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     6→\n     7→/** DTO for a leg in an itinerary. */\n     8→public class Leg implements Serializable {\n     9→\n    10→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→  private final String voyageNumber;\n    12→  private final Location from;\n    13→  private final Location to;\n    14→  private final String loadTime;\n    15→  private final String unloadTime;\n    16→\n    17→  public Leg(\n    18→      String voyageNumber,\n    19→      Location from,\n    20→      Location to,\n    21→      LocalDateTime loadTime,\n    22→      LocalDateTime unloadTime) {\n    23→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    24→    this.from = from;\n    25→    this.to = to;\n    26→    this.loadTime = DateConverter.toString(loadTime);\n    27→    this.unloadTime = DateConverter.toString(unloadTime);\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n    31→    return voyageNumber;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  public String getFrom() {\n    35→    return from.toString();\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public String getFromUnLocode() {\n    39→    return from.getUnLocode();\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public String getFromName() {\n    43→    return from.getName();\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public String getTo() {\n    47→    return to.toString();\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public String getToName() {\n    51→    return to.getName();\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public String getToUnLocode() {\n    55→    return to.getUnLocode();\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public String getLoadTime() {\n    59→    return loadTime;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public String getUnloadTime() {\n    63→    return unloadTime;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public String toString() {\n    68→    return \"Leg{\"\n    69→        + \"voyageNumber=\"\n    70→        + voyageNumber\n    71→        + \", from=\"\n    72→        + from.getUnLocode()\n    73→        + \", to=\"\n    74→        + to.getUnLocode()\n    75→        + \", loadTime=\"\n    76→        + loadTime\n    77→        + \", unloadTime=\"\n    78→        + unloadTime\n    79→        + '}';\n    80→  }\n    81→}\n    82→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"975a1745-bc6d-40d0-bb01-68d8332e39d7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T4u2TDaXiLzDj1wXGWYfBv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→\n     5→/** Location DTO. */\n     6→public class Location implements Serializable {\n     7→\n     8→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     9→\n    10→  private String unLocode;\n    11→  private String name;\n    12→\n    13→  public Location(String unLocode, String name) {\n    14→    this.unLocode = unLocode;\n    15→    this.name = name;\n    16→  }\n    17→\n    18→  public String getUnLocode() {\n    19→    return unLocode;\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  public String getName() {\n    23→    return name;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  @Override\n    27→  public String toString() {\n    28→    return name + \" (\" + unLocode + \")\";\n    29→  }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"f478ddde-a7d3-4a13-917d-43423902b752"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019wwpeZ3xu5bU61f1esSYfj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→public class TrackingEvents {\n     4→\n     5→  private final boolean expected;\n     6→  private final String description;\n     7→  private final String time;\n     8→\n     9→  public TrackingEvents(boolean expected, String description, String time) {\n    10→    this.expected = expected;\n    11→    this.description = description;\n    12→    this.time = time;\n    13→  }\n    14→\n    15→  public boolean isExpected() {\n    16→    return expected;\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public String getDescription() {\n    20→    return description;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public String getTime() {\n    24→    return time;\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"40a02976-a35f-42f7-87a7-00cf4ab369ce"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D9Rp6gW3rUb7ULfjWL3v4D","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class CdiApplicationEvents implements ApplicationEvents {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    Logger logger;\n    18→\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    Event<CargoHandledEvent> cargoHandledEvent;\n    21→\n    22→    @Inject\n    23→    Event<CargoMisdirectedEvent> cargoMisdirectedEvent;\n    24→\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    Event<CargoArrivedEvent> cargoArrivedEvent;\n    27→\n    28→    @Inject\n    29→    Event<HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt> handlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent;\n    30→\n    31→    @Override\n    32→    public void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event) {\n    33→        Cargo cargo = event.getCargo();\n    34→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was handled {0}\", cargo);\n    35→        cargoHandledEvent.fire(new CargoHandledEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    @Override\n    39→    public void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo) {\n    40→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was misdirected {0}\", cargo);\n    41→        cargoMisdirectedEvent.fire(new CargoMisdirectedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    @Override\n    45→    public void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo) {\n    46→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo has arrived {0}\", cargo);\n    47→        cargoArrivedEvent.fire(new CargoArrivedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @Override\n    51→    public void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) {\n    52→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Received handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n    53→        handlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent.fire(attempt);\n    54→    }\n    55→}\n    56→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"72947d02-df4c-4f9f-8ae0-8c407dd4f3fd"}
