{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0141sJRxcGxNRbL7CpN6YYGL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→  xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→  <groupId>org.eclipse.ee4j</groupId>\n     6→  <artifactId>cargo-tracker</artifactId>\n     7→  <version>2.2-SNAPSHOT</version>\n     8→  <packaging>jar</packaging>\n     9→  <name>Eclipse Cargo Tracker</name>\n    10→  <description>The project demonstrates how you can develop applications with Quarkus using widely adopted architectural best practices like Domain-Driven Design (DDD).</description>\n    11→\n    12→  <properties>\n    13→    <compiler-plugin.version>3.13.0</compiler-plugin.version>\n    14→    <maven.compiler.release>17</maven.compiler.release>\n    15→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    16→    <project.reporting.outputEncoding>UTF-8</project.reporting.outputEncoding>\n    17→    <quarkus.platform.artifact-id>quarkus-bom</quarkus.platform.artifact-id>\n    18→    <quarkus.platform.group-id>io.quarkus.platform</quarkus.platform.group-id>\n    19→    <quarkus.platform.version>3.17.7</quarkus.platform.version>\n    20→    <surefire-plugin.version>3.5.2</surefire-plugin.version>\n    21→  </properties>\n    22→\n    23→  <dependencyManagement>\n    24→    <dependencies>\n    25→      <dependency>\n    26→        <groupId>${quarkus.platform.group-id}</groupId>\n    27→        <artifactId>${quarkus.platform.artifact-id}</artifactId>\n    28→        <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n    29→        <type>pom</type>\n    30→        <scope>import</scope>\n    31→      </dependency>\n    32→    </dependencies>\n    33→  </dependencyManagement>\n    34→\n    35→  <dependencies>\n    36→    <!-- Quarkus RESTEasy Reactive with Jackson -->\n    37→    <dependency>\n    38→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    39→      <artifactId>quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson</artifactId>\n    40→    </dependency>\n    41→\n    42→    <!-- Quarkus Hibernate ORM with Panache -->\n    43→    <dependency>\n    44→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    45→      <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm</artifactId>\n    46→    </dependency>\n    47→\n    48→    <!-- H2 Database -->\n    49→    <dependency>\n    50→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    51→      <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-h2</artifactId>\n    52→    </dependency>\n    53→\n    54→    <!-- CDI / Arc -->\n    55→    <dependency>\n    56→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    57→      <artifactId>quarkus-arc</artifactId>\n    58→    </dependency>\n    59→\n    60→    <!-- Bean Validation -->\n    61→    <dependency>\n    62→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    63→      <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-validator</artifactId>\n    64→    </dependency>\n    65→\n    66→    <!-- Scheduler (replaces Jakarta Batch / EJB Timer) -->\n    67→    <dependency>\n    68→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    69→      <artifactId>quarkus-scheduler</artifactId>\n    70→    </dependency>\n    71→\n    72→    <!-- Quarkus REST Client (replaces JAX-RS Client) -->\n    73→    <dependency>\n    74→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    75→      <artifactId>quarkus-rest-client-reactive-jackson</artifactId>\n    76→    </dependency>\n    77→\n    78→    <!-- Quarkus Narayana JTA (Transactions) -->\n    79→    <dependency>\n    80→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    81→      <artifactId>quarkus-narayana-jta</artifactId>\n    82→    </dependency>\n    83→\n    84→    <!-- SSE support is included with RESTEasy Reactive -->\n    85→\n    86→    <!-- Smallrye Health -->\n    87→    <dependency>\n    88→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    89→      <artifactId>quarkus-smallrye-health</artifactId>\n    90→    </dependency>\n    91→\n    92→    <!-- Apache Commons Lang3 -->\n    93→    <dependency>\n    94→      <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>\n    95→      <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>\n    96→      <version>3.18.0</version>\n    97→    </dependency>\n    98→\n    99→    <!-- JAXB for XML support -->\n   100→    <dependency>\n   101→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n   102→      <artifactId>quarkus-jaxb</artifactId>\n   103→    </dependency>\n   104→\n   105→    <!-- Test dependencies -->\n   106→    <dependency>\n   107→      <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n   108→      <artifactId>quarkus-junit5</artifactId>\n   109→      <scope>test</scope>\n   110→    </dependency>\n   111→    <dependency>\n   112→      <groupId>io.rest-assured</groupId>\n   113→      <artifactId>rest-assured</artifactId>\n   114→      <scope>test</scope>\n   115→    </dependency>\n   116→  </dependencies>\n   117→\n   118→  <build>\n   119→    <finalName>cargo-tracker</finalName>\n   120→    <plugins>\n   121→      <plugin>\n   122→        <groupId>${quarkus.platform.group-id}</groupId>\n   123→        <artifactId>quarkus-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n   124→        <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n   125→        <extensions>true</extensions>\n   126→        <executions>\n   127→          <execution>\n   128→            <goals>\n   129→              <goal>build</goal>\n   130→              <goal>generate-code</goal>\n   131→              <goal>generate-code-tests</goal>\n   132→            </goals>\n   133→          </execution>\n   134→        </executions>\n   135→      </plugin>\n   136→      <plugin>\n   137→        <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n   138→        <version>${compiler-plugin.version}</version>\n   139→        <configuration>\n   140→          <parameters>true</parameters>\n   141→        </configuration>\n   142→      </plugin>\n   143→      <plugin>\n   144→        <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>\n   145→        <version>${surefire-plugin.version}</version>\n   146→        <configuration>\n   147→          <systemPropertyVariables>\n   148→            <java.util.logging.manager>org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager</java.util.logging.manager>\n   149→            <maven.home>${maven.home}</maven.home>\n   150→          </systemPropertyVariables>\n   151→        </configuration>\n   152→      </plugin>\n   153→    </plugins>\n   154→  </build>\n   155→</project>\n   156→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"fd73038a-6018-4637-9556-8afce1c9e8fb"}
