{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The conversation is summarized below:\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the entire conversation:\n\n1. **Initial Request**: The user asked me to migrate a Java application from Jakarta EE to Quarkus. This is a comprehensive migration with a detailed checklist including analyzing codebase, generating smoke tests, updating dependencies, refactoring code, modifying build configs/Dockerfile, building Docker image, running tests, and documenting everything.\n\n2. **Codebase Analysis Phase**: \n   - Explored the project structure at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output`\n   - This is the Eclipse Cargo Tracker application - a DDD reference implementation\n   - Identified technologies: Jakarta EE 8 (javax namespace), EJB, JMS, JPA, JSF/PrimeFaces, JAX-RS, Jakarta Batch, CDI, Bean Validation, SSE\n   - Read pom.xml, Dockerfile, persistence.xml, web.xml, beans.xml, faces-config.xml\n   - Read all ~104 Java source files across packages\n\n3. **Migration Strategy**:\n   - EJB @Stateless → CDI @ApplicationScoped + @Transactional\n   - EJB @Singleton @Startup → @ApplicationScoped + io.quarkus.runtime.Startup\n   - JMS → CDI Events (in-process)\n   - JSF → Remove, replace with REST endpoints\n   - JPA → Quarkus Hibernate ORM with H2\n   - Jakarta Batch → Quarkus Scheduler\n   - JAX-RS → Quarkus RESTEasy Reactive\n   - SSE → Simplified REST endpoint\n   - All javax.* → jakarta.* namespace\n\n4. **pom.xml Creation**: Created new Quarkus pom.xml with dependencies including quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson, quarkus-hibernate-orm, quarkus-jdbc-h2, quarkus-arc, quarkus-hibernate-validator, quarkus-scheduler, quarkus-rest-client-reactive-jackson, quarkus-narayana-jta, quarkus-smallrye-health, commons-lang3, quarkus-jaxb, quarkus-junit5, rest-assured. Java 17, Quarkus 3.17.7.\n\n5. **Application Properties**: Created src/main/resources/application.properties with H2 in-memory datasource, Hibernate ORM config, graph traversal URL config.\n\n6. **import.sql**: Created src/main/resources/import.sql with initial data.\n\n7. **Parallel Refactoring** (4 agents):\n   - Application layer: Updated BookingService, HandlingEventService, CargoInspectionService, ApplicationEvents, DefaultBookingService, DefaultCargoInspectionService, DefaultHandlingEventService, ApplicationSettings, DateConverter, RestConfiguration, SampleDataGenerator\n   - Domain model: Updated ~20 files including Cargo, Delivery, HandlingActivity, Itinerary, Leg, RouteSpecification, TrackingId, HandlingEvent, HandlingEventFactory, CannotCreateHandlingEventException, Location, UnLocode, Voyage, VoyageNumber, Schedule, CarrierMovement\n   - Infrastructure: Created CdiApplicationEvents, CargoHandledEvent, CargoMisdirectedEvent, CargoArrivedEvent, CargoEventObservers. Stubbed out old JMS files. Updated LoggerProducer, CargoUpdated, all JPA repositories, ExternalRoutingService\n   - Interfaces: Updated HandlingReportService, HandlingReport, GraphTraversalService, TransitPath, TransitEdge, GraphDao, RealtimeCargoTrackingService, DefaultBookingServiceFacade, assemblers. Created BookingRestService, BookCargoRequest, BookCargoResponse, EventFileProcessor. Stubbed JSF beans, batch files. Updated UploadDirectoryScanner.\n\n8. **Verification**: Grep confirmed no remaining javax.* imports, no @Stateless, @MessageDriven, javax.faces, javax.batch, javax.jms, or @PersistenceContext references.\n\n9. **Post-refactoring Fixes**:\n   - Replaced ExternalRoutingService to call GraphTraversalService directly (in-process) instead of via JAX-RS client REST call\n   - Simplified RealtimeCargoTrackingService to return JSON list instead of SSE (removed SSE complexity)\n   - Removed quarkus-rest-client-reactive-jackson dependency since no longer needed\n   - Created beans.xml for CDI\n   - Removed old webapp, persistence.xml, batch-jobs, test files, liberty config\n\n10. **Dockerfile**: Updated to use maven:3.9.9-eclipse-temurin-17, Java 17, builds with `mvn -B -DskipTests package`, runs with `java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar`\n\n11. **Smoke Tests**: Created smoke/pyproject.toml and smoke/smoke.py with 11 tests covering health checks, cargo listing, location listing, tracking IDs, cargo details, cargo tracking, graph traversal, handling reports, and cargo tracking endpoint.\n\n12. **First Build Attempt**: Failed with error `'dependencies.dependency.version' for io.quarkus:quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson:jar is missing. @ line 37, column 17` - this suggests the BOM isn't resolving properly or the artifact name changed in Quarkus 3.17.\n\n13. **Current State**: Was about to investigate and fix the dependency resolution issue. In Quarkus 3.9+, `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson` was renamed to `quarkus-rest-jackson`. The BOM might not include the old artifact name.\n\nKey files that were created/modified:\n- pom.xml (complete rewrite)\n- Dockerfile (complete rewrite)\n- src/main/resources/application.properties (new)\n- src/main/resources/import.sql (new)\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/beans.xml (new)\n- smoke/pyproject.toml (new)\n- smoke/smoke.py (new)\n- All ~104 Java source files (javax→jakarta, EJB→CDI, JMS→CDI Events, etc.)\n- New files: CdiApplicationEvents.java, CargoHandledEvent.java, CargoMisdirectedEvent.java, CargoArrivedEvent.java, CargoEventObservers.java, BookingRestService.java, BookCargoRequest.java, BookCargoResponse.java, EventFileProcessor.java\n\nRemoved:\n- src/main/webapp (entire directory)\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml\n- src/main/resources/META-INF/batch-jobs\n- src/test (entire directory)\n- src/main/liberty\n\nDocker environment variables:\n- SCARF_IMAGE_TAG=\"scarf_1773478429_1235849:latest\"\n- SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME=\"scarf_1773478429_1235849_app\"\n\nNote: First build attempt used literal tag `cargo-tracker-quarkus:latest` due to env var issues in shell.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user requested an autonomous, one-shot migration of the Eclipse Cargo Tracker Java application from Jakarta EE to Quarkus. The detailed checklist includes: analyzing the codebase, generating smoke tests, updating project dependencies, refactoring all code, modifying build configs and Dockerfile, building a Docker image, running the container, executing smoke tests, addressing errors, and documenting everything in CHANGELOG.md. Docker isolation requirements mandate using `$SCARF_IMAGE_TAG` and `$SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME` env vars with dynamic port allocation (`-p 0:8080`).\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Jakarta EE 8 (javax namespace) → Quarkus 3.17.7 (jakarta namespace)\n   - EJB (@Stateless, @Singleton, @Startup, @MessageDriven) → CDI (@ApplicationScoped, @Transactional, io.quarkus.runtime.Startup)\n   - JMS queues/consumers → CDI Events (@Observes, Event.fire())\n   - JSF/PrimeFaces → REST endpoints (BookingRestService)\n   - Jakarta Batch → Quarkus @Scheduled + EventFileProcessor\n   - JPA with persistence.xml → Quarkus Hibernate ORM via application.properties\n   - JAX-RS Client → Direct in-process service calls\n   - SSE with SseBroadcaster → Simplified JSON REST endpoint\n   - @PersistenceContext → @Inject EntityManager\n   - @Resource JNDI lookups → @ConfigProperty (MicroProfile Config)\n   - Domain-Driven Design (DDD) architecture with aggregate roots, repositories, specifications\n   - H2 in-memory database\n   - WAR packaging → JAR packaging (Quarkus fast-jar)\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **pom.xml** (Complete rewrite for Quarkus)\n     - Changed packaging from WAR to JAR, Java 8 to 17\n     - Replaced Jakarta EE API + Payara/OpenLiberty profiles with Quarkus BOM and extensions\n     - Current dependencies: quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson, quarkus-hibernate-orm, quarkus-jdbc-h2, quarkus-arc, quarkus-hibernate-validator, quarkus-scheduler, quarkus-narayana-jta, quarkus-smallrye-health, quarkus-jaxb, commons-lang3\n     - **CRITICAL**: The artifact `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson` is failing dependency resolution - likely needs to be renamed to `quarkus-rest-jackson` for Quarkus 3.9+\n     ```xml\n     <quarkus.platform.version>3.17.7</quarkus.platform.version>\n     <maven.compiler.release>17</maven.compiler.release>\n     ```\n\n   - **Dockerfile** (Complete rewrite for Quarkus)\n     - Base image: `maven:3.9.9-eclipse-temurin-17`\n     - Builds with `mvn -B -DskipTests package`\n     - Runs with `java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar`\n     ```dockerfile\n     FROM maven:3.9.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\n     USER root\n     RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 python3-venv python3-pip curl && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n     RUN curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh && ln -s /root/.cargo/bin/uv /usr/local/bin/uv\n     WORKDIR /workspace\n     COPY pom.xml .\n     COPY src ./src\n     COPY smoke ./smoke\n     RUN mvn -B -DskipTests package\n     CMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar\"]\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/resources/application.properties** (New)\n     - H2 in-memory datasource, Hibernate ORM drop-and-create, import.sql, graph traversal URL\n     ```properties\n     quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n     quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:cargotracker;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n     quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n     quarkus.hibernate-orm.sql-load-script=import.sql\n     graph.traversal.url=http://localhost:${quarkus.http.port}/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/resources/import.sql** (New)\n     ```sql\n     INSERT INTO applicationsettings (id, sampleloaded) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n     ```\n\n   - **src/main/resources/META-INF/beans.xml** (New - CDI config for Quarkus)\n\n   - **Infrastructure Messaging - New CDI Event System** (Replaces JMS):\n     - `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CdiApplicationEvents.java` - Implements ApplicationEvents using CDI Event.fire()\n     - `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CargoHandledEvent.java` - Event DTO with trackingId\n     - `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CargoMisdirectedEvent.java` - Event DTO with trackingId\n     - `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CargoArrivedEvent.java` - Event DTO with trackingId\n     - `src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/CargoEventObservers.java` - @Observes methods replacing all 5 JMS MessageDriven consumers\n\n   - **Old JMS files** (Stubbed out with empty classes):\n     - JmsApplicationEvents.java, CargoHandledConsumer.java, DeliveredCargoConsumer.java, MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java, RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java, HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java\n\n   - **ExternalRoutingService.java** (Major refactoring)\n     - Changed from JAX-RS Client REST call to direct @Inject of GraphTraversalService (in-process)\n     - Removed @Resource JNDI lookup, removed ClientBuilder usage\n     ```java\n     @ApplicationScoped\n     public class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n         @Inject GraphTraversalService graphTraversalService;\n         @Inject LocationRepository locationRepository;\n         @Inject VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n         // Calls graphTraversalService.findShortestPath() directly\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java** (Simplified for Quarkus)\n     - Removed SSE broadcaster/SseEventSink complexity\n     - Now returns List<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> as JSON\n     ```java\n     @ApplicationScoped @Path(\"/cargo\")\n     public class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n         @GET @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n         public List<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> tracking() { ... }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **BookingRestService.java** (New - replaces JSF UI)\n     - REST endpoints: GET /booking/cargos, GET /booking/locations, GET /booking/cargos/{id}, GET /booking/tracking/{id}, POST /booking/cargos, GET /booking/cargos/{id}/routes, PUT /booking/cargos/{id}/route, GET /booking/trackingids\n   - **BookCargoRequest.java** (New DTO)\n   - **BookCargoResponse.java** (New DTO)\n\n   - **EventFileProcessor.java** (New - replaces Jakarta Batch)\n     - Simple file processing with BufferedReader, replaces batch job XML + EventItemReader/Writer\n\n   - **UploadDirectoryScanner.java** (Refactored)\n     - EJB @Schedule → Quarkus @Scheduled(every = \"120s\")\n\n   - **SampleDataGenerator.java** (Refactored)\n     - @Singleton @Startup → @ApplicationScoped @Startup (io.quarkus.runtime.Startup)\n     - @TransactionAttribute → @Transactional\n     - @PersistenceContext → @Inject EntityManager\n\n   - **All JPA Repositories** (JpaCargoRepository, JpaHandlingEventRepository, JpaLocationRepository, JpaVoyageRepository)\n     - javax→jakarta namespace, @PersistenceContext → @Inject\n\n   - **All domain entities** (Cargo, Delivery, HandlingActivity, Itinerary, Leg, RouteSpecification, TrackingId, HandlingEvent, Location, UnLocode, Voyage, VoyageNumber, Schedule, CarrierMovement)\n     - javax.persistence→jakarta.persistence, javax.validation→jakarta.validation\n\n   - **All application services** (DefaultBookingService, DefaultCargoInspectionService, DefaultHandlingEventService)\n     - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped @Transactional\n\n   - **REST endpoints** (HandlingReportService, GraphTraversalService)\n     - @Stateless → @ApplicationScoped, javax→jakarta\n\n   - **JSF beans** (11 files stubbed out as empty classes)\n     - ListCargo, Booking, Track, CargoDetails, ChangeDestination, ChangeDestinationDialog, ChangeArrivalDeadline, ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog, ItinerarySelection, FacesConfiguration, EventLogger, tracking/web/Track\n\n   - **smoke/smoke.py** (New - 11 smoke tests)\n     - Tests: health check, health ready, health live, list cargos, list locations, list tracking IDs, get cargo details, track cargo, graph traversal, handling report submission, cargo tracking endpoint\n\n   - **Removed directories/files**:\n     - src/main/webapp (entire JSF/XHTML web content)\n     - src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml\n     - src/main/resources/META-INF/batch-jobs/\n     - src/test/ (old Arquillian tests)\n     - src/main/liberty/\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   - **Docker build error - environment variables not resolving**: `docker build -t $SCARF_IMAGE_TAG .` failed with \"repository name must have at least one component\". Even explicit export didn't work. Used literal tag `cargo-tracker-quarkus:latest` as workaround to verify build.\n   - **Maven dependency resolution error (CURRENT)**: `'dependencies.dependency.version' for io.quarkus:quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson:jar is missing. @ line 37, column 17`. The Quarkus BOM (3.17.7) does not contain `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson` - this artifact was renamed to `quarkus-rest-jackson` starting from Quarkus 3.9. Similarly, other `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-*` artifacts were renamed to `quarkus-rest-*`. This needs to be fixed in pom.xml.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - **Solved**: Eliminated all javax.* imports across 104+ Java files (confirmed via grep)\n   - **Solved**: Replaced JMS messaging with CDI Events (5 queue consumers → 1 observer class)\n   - **Solved**: Replaced JSF UI with REST API endpoints\n   - **Solved**: Replaced Jakarta Batch with Quarkus Scheduler + EventFileProcessor\n   - **Solved**: Eliminated JAX-RS Client dependency by calling GraphTraversalService directly\n   - **Solved**: Simplified SSE to plain JSON REST endpoint\n   - **Ongoing**: Maven build fails due to incorrect artifact name `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson` (should be `quarkus-rest-jackson` for Quarkus 3.9+)\n   - **Potential issue not yet addressed**: DTOs (RouteCandidate, CargoRoute, Leg, Location, CargoStatus, TrackingEvents) lack default constructors needed for Jackson deserialization\n\n6. All User Messages:\n   - Message 1: Detailed migration instructions from Jakarta EE to Quarkus with comprehensive checklist, environment constraints, Docker isolation requirements ($SCARF_CONTAINER_NAME, $SCARF_IMAGE_TAG, -p 0:8080), migration workflow (5 phases), validation protocol, error handling requirements, and output format specifications.\n   - Message 2: (empty - just system reminder about TodoWrite)\n   - Message 3: (empty - just system reminder about TodoWrite)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Fix the Maven dependency resolution error (`quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson` → `quarkus-rest-jackson` and similar renames)\n   - Potentially add default constructors to DTO classes for Jackson\n   - Successfully build the Docker image\n   - Run the container with dynamic port allocation\n   - Execute smoke tests against the running container\n   - Create CHANGELOG.md documenting all actions, errors, and resolutions\n   - Produce final migration report in specified Markdown format\n\n8. Current Work:\n   The most recent work was attempting to build the Docker image and encountering the Maven dependency resolution error. The build failed because `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson` is not found in the Quarkus 3.17.7 BOM. This is the artifact naming change that happened in Quarkus 3.9 where `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-*` was renamed to `quarkus-rest-*`.\n\n   The last command run was:\n   ```bash\n   docker build -t cargo-tracker-quarkus:latest /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/ 2>&1 | tail -200\n   ```\n   \n   Error output:\n   ```\n   [ERROR] 'dependencies.dependency.version' for io.quarkus:quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson:jar is missing. @ line 37, column 17\n   ```\n   \n   A web search was attempted to find the correct artifact name but the API returned an error.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Fix the pom.xml dependency names. In Quarkus 3.9+, the artifacts were renamed:\n   - `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson` → `quarkus-rest-jackson`\n   - `quarkus-rest-client-reactive-jackson` → `quarkus-rest-client-jackson` (already removed)\n   \n   Also need to check if other artifact names changed: `quarkus-resteasy-reactive` → `quarkus-rest`. Then rebuild the Docker image and continue with the migration checklist.\n\n   The task being worked on immediately before this summary: \"Build the application as a Docker image\" from the migration checklist, which failed due to the dependency naming issue. The error was: `'dependencies.dependency.version' for io.quarkus:quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jackson:jar is missing. @ line 37, column 17`.\nPlease continue the conversation from where we left it off without asking the user any further questions. Continue with the last task that you were asked to work on."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a9b0dd0-5198-4e27-99cf-ce225aa708f6","uuid":"8025b520-111e-490b-9596-d88becdc1374","isSynthetic":true}
